3	Porsche 992 GT3 Cup - AFM Chassis 002	porsche-992-gt3-cup-002	WP0ZZZ99ZNS298002	992 GT3 Cup	Type 992	Development Car and Second Entry	Second Porsche 992 GT3 Cup chassis operated by AF Motorsport, serving dual roles as the team's development platform for setup experimentation and as the race entry for the team's second driver in selected Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica events. This chassis enables the team to field two-car entries at major events while providing a dedicated platform for testing new setup directions without compromising the primary car's race preparation.	Active	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Chassis 002 joined AF Motorsport in July 2025 as a mid-season addition to support the team's expanding competitive program. The car was acquired with limited previous use from a European Carrera Cup team upgrading their fleet. Upon arrival, the chassis underwent comprehensive inspection and refresh at AF Motorsport's Estoril workshop, including gearbox rebuild, damper servicing, and installation of team-standard data acquisition equipment. Chassis 002 made its competition debut with AF Motorsport at the Portimão round of the 2025 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica, finishing fourth in class. Throughout the remainder of the 2025 season, this chassis was used extensively for setup development work during private testing, with findings directly benefiting the performance of the primary car. For the 2026 season, Chassis 002 will serve as the race entry for the team's second driver at selected events while continuing its development role. The car carries secondary team livery with space allocated for additional partner branding.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Chassis & Aerodynamics	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	porsche-992-gt3-cup---afm-chassis-002	2026-04-10 10:36:29.379+05:30	2026-04-09 19:16:06.195+05:30
2	Porsche 991.2 GT3 Cup - AFM Chassis 003	porsche-991-2-gt3-cup-003	WP0ZZZ99ZJS198103	991.2 GT3 Cup	Type 991.2	Heritage Car and Training Platform	Previous-generation Porsche 991.2 GT3 Cup car retained by AF Motorsport for driver training, corporate events, and heritage activities. This chassis represents the platform on which André Fernandes achieved significant success before the team's transition to the 992 generation. The car remains fully race-ready and provides an accessible entry point for drivers transitioning to Porsche Cup competition or for corporate partner driving experiences.	Active	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Chassis 003 was acquired new by AF Motorsport in 2019 and served as the team's primary competition car through the 2024 season. During its competitive career, this chassis achieved eight race victories, fifteen podium finishes, and two track records across Portuguese and Spanish Porsche Cup competitions. The car completed over 4,500 competitive kilometers without major mechanical failure, testament to AF Motorsport's preparation standards and the inherent durability of the Porsche Cup platform. Following the introduction of the 992-generation cars, Chassis 003 was transitioned to a training and heritage role. The car underwent comprehensive preservation-level service in late 2024 including engine refresh, gearbox inspection, damper rebuild, and complete systems check. For the 2026 season, Chassis 003 supports AF Motorsport's driver development programs, providing seat time for aspiring drivers in a cost-effective yet highly capable platform. The car appears in heritage livery commemorating AF Motorsport's early competitive achievements.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Chassis & Aerodynamics	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	porsche-9912-gt3-cup---afm-chassis-003	2026-04-10 10:36:07.207+05:30	2026-04-09 19:16:03.66+05:30
1	Radical SR3 XX - AFM Driver Development Car	radical-sr3-xx-001	SR3XX2024001	SR3 XX	2024 Specification	Pure Driving Experience - The Ultimate Training Tool	Radical SR3 XX acquired for AF Motorsport's driver development and track day programs. This purpose-built sports racer provides an unfiltered driving experience with exceptional feedback, high downforce, and a power-to-weight ratio exceeding many GT cars. The SR3 XX serves as an ideal stepping stone between karting and GT racing, developing fundamental skills including high-downforce cornering technique, precise throttle application, and aerodynamic sensitivity awareness.	Active	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Acquired new from Radical Portugal in early 2024 as part of AF Motorsport's expanded driver development initiative. The SR3 XX was selected following extensive evaluation of available training platforms, with the car's combination of accessibility, feedback quality, and direct relevance to GT racing technique making it the optimal choice. The chassis was delivered in base specification and prepared at AF Motorsport's Estoril workshop with team-standard data acquisition, radio communications, and video systems. Throughout 2024, the car completed over 2,500 kilometers of development activity across Portuguese circuits, supporting driver coaching programs and providing seat time for team members and partner guests. For the 2025-2026 period, the SR3 XX continues as the cornerstone of AF Motorsport's driver development curriculum, with structured programs designed to accelerate the progression from karting to Porsche Cup competition.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Power Unit / Engine	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	radical-sr3-xx---afm-driver-development-car	2026-04-10 10:35:40.748+05:30	2026-04-09 19:15:29.724+05:30
5	Formula 4 Tatuus T-421 - AFM Academy Car	formula-4-tatuus-001	T421-2023-089	Tatuus T-421	FIA Formula 4 Specification	Single-Seater Foundation - Pathway to Formula Racing	FIA-homologated Formula 4 car operated by AF Motorsport for single-seater driver development and academy programs. The Tatuus T-421 represents the current generation of Formula 4 chassis, featuring the halo safety device, enhanced crash protection, and a sophisticated aerodynamic package. This car provides AF Motorsport drivers with authentic single-seater experience, developing skills essential for progression through the formula racing ladder including precise racing line discipline, high-downforce cornering technique, and open-wheel spatial awareness.	Active	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Chassis T421-2023-089 was acquired in late 2023 as AF Motorsport expanded its driver development offerings to include single-seater training. The car had completed a partial season in the Spanish Formula 4 Championship before joining the AF Motorsport fleet, providing a proven platform with known performance characteristics. Upon acquisition, the chassis underwent comprehensive inspection and refresh including engine dyno verification, gearbox service, and installation of AF Motorsport's data and video systems. Throughout 2024, the car supported individual driver development programs and served as the platform for AF Motorsport's Formula Academy initiative—a structured program introducing karting graduates to single-seater technique. For the 2025-2026 period, the T-421 continues to provide single-seater training capability, with availability for individual coaching, track days, and potential competitive entries in national Formula 4 events.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Electronic Systems / ECU	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	formula-4-tatuus-t-421---afm-academy-car	2026-04-10 10:37:11.558+05:30	2026-04-09 19:16:20.83+05:30
4	Porsche 992 GT3 Cup - AFM Chassis 001	porsche-992-gt3-cup-001	WP0ZZZ99ZNS298001	992 GT3 Cup	Type 992	The Flagship - AF Motorsport's Primary Race Car	Primary competition vehicle for AF Motorsport's Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica campaign. This Porsche 992 GT3 Cup represents the latest generation of Porsche's highly successful one-make racing platform, featuring significant advancements over the previous 991.2 generation including improved aerodynamics, enhanced safety systems, and a broader operating window that makes the car more accessible while maintaining the challenging characteristics that develop driver skill. Chassis 001 serves as the team's benchmark car for setup development and performance validation.	Active	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "This chassis was delivered new to AF Motorsport in February 2025 as part of the team's expansion into the Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica. The car completed its initial shakedown at Autódromo do Estoril under the supervision of Porsche Motorsport engineers, immediately demonstrating the expected performance characteristics. Throughout the 2025 season, Chassis 001 competed in six race weekends across Portugal and Spain, securing two race victories and four additional podium finishes. The car underwent comprehensive off-season rebuild in November 2025, including gearbox refresh, damper dyno verification, and full systems inspection. For the 2026 season, the car has been updated with the latest Porsche Motorsport software calibrations and setup refinements developed during winter testing. Chassis 001 carries the primary team livery and serves as the lead entry for André Fernandes in the 2026 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Drivetrain & Transmission	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	porsche-992-gt3-cup---afm-chassis-001	2026-04-10 10:57:42.026+05:30	2026-04-09 19:16:15.798+05:30
6	Porsche 991.2 GT3 R - AFM Chassis 001	porsche-991-2-gt3-r-afm	WP0ZZZ99ZKS198201	991.2 GT3 R	Type 991.2	Porsche's GT3 Contender	The Porsche 991.2 GT3 R is a thoroughbred GT3 racing machine developed by Porsche Motorsport for international GT3 competition. Based on the 911 GT3 RS production car, it features a 4.0-liter flat-six engine producing over 500 horsepower, a sequential six-speed gearbox, and comprehensive aerodynamic package optimized for endurance racing. This chassis is campaigned by AF Motorsport in International GT Open and selected endurance events.	Active	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "This Porsche 991.2 GT3 R chassis was acquired by AF Motorsport in late 2025 as part of the team's expansion into premier GT3 competition. The car had previously competed in European GT Open and 24H Series events with a German team, arriving with known history and proven reliability.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    AF Motorsport's preparation included comprehensive refresh of all systems, installation of team-standard data acquisition and communication equipment, and application of AF Motorsport's distinctive livery. The car made its AF Motorsport debut at the International GT Open Portimão round with drivers André Fernandes and Angelo Fontana.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The chassis represents AF Motorsport's entry into top-level GT3 competition and provides a platform for driver progression to the highest categories of international GT racing.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	porsche-9912-gt3-r---afm-chassis-001	2026-04-10 16:06:59.906+05:30	2026-04-10 16:05:07.28+05:30
7	Mercedes-AMG GT3	mercedes-amg-gt3-winter	AMGGT3-2024-045	AMG GT3	Evo	Affalterbach's GT Weapon	The Mercedes-AMG GT3 is a front-engine GT3 race car developed by Mercedes-AMG, featuring a 6.2-liter V8 engine and sophisticated aerodynamics. Pipo Massa competes with this machinery in the GT Winter Series, expanding his experience across multiple GT platforms as part of his comprehensive driver development program.	Active	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Pipo Massa's Winter Series program includes seat time in Mercedes-AMG GT3 machinery, providing valuable experience in front-engine GT car dynamics. The contrasting characteristics between Porsche's rear-engine platform and Mercedes' front-mid engine layout accelerate driver development by building adaptability and broadening technical understanding.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    This experience aligns with AF Motorsport's philosophy of developing complete racing professionals capable of extracting performance from diverse machinery types. The Winter Series campaign provided competitive mileage and continued progression in Pipo's young career.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	mercedes-amg-gt3	2026-04-10 16:08:42.01+05:30	2026-04-10 16:08:42.009+05:30
