5	Circuit de Spa-Francorchamps	spa	SPA	SPA	The Greatest Racing Circuit in the World	Legendary permanent racing circuit located in the Ardennes forest of eastern Belgium. Spa-Francorchamps is universally regarded as one of motorsport's greatest challenges and most beloved venues. The original 14-kilometer public road circuit hosted racing from 1921, with the modern 7-kilometer permanent configuration opening in 1979 and hosting the Belgian Formula 1 Grand Prix continuously since 1985. The circuit is defined by its spectacular setting in the Ardennes forest, dramatic elevation changes, and the world-famous Eau Rouge-Raidillon complex—a high-speed compression and climb that tests both driver commitment and vehicle capability like no other corner sequence in motorsport. Spa's microclimate means conditions can change rapidly, with rain possible on one section of the circuit while another remains dry.	permanent	7.004	4.352	19	2	clockwise	1	102	70000	0101000020E61000006D567DAEB6E21740D5E76A2BF6374940	Route du Circuit 55, 4970 Stavelot	172	1921-08-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	2	4	https://www.spa-francorchamps.be	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The Ardennes' Sacred Ground", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "Circuit de Spa-Francorchamps embodies motorsport's romantic ideal—a circuit carved through forest and countryside, demanding respect from every driver who tackles its challenging layout. The original 14-kilometer triangle of public roads produced heroes and tragedies in equal measure, with drivers of the golden era describing Spa as the ultimate test of courage and machine.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "The modern 7-kilometer circuit preserves the essential character of the original while meeting contemporary safety standards. Eau Rouge-Raidillon remains the circuit's defining challenge—a high-speed left-right-left compression taken at over 300 km/h in modern Formula 1 cars, generating sustained g-forces that compress drivers into their seats while the car fights for grip through the climb. The long Kemmel straight, high-speed Pouhon double-left, and flat-out Blanchimont corner complete a layout that rewards bravery while punishing mistakes severely.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "For AF Motorsport, Spa represents the ultimate challenge on the European calendar. The circuit's length and complexity demand exceptional preparation, while its unpredictable weather requires strategic flexibility and driver adaptability. A strong performance at Spa validates every aspect of team operation—engineering, driver coaching, and race strategy.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Circuit length and complexity require extensive preparation. Weather monitoring essential—conditions can change within minutes. Eau Rouge-Raidillon setup critical: car must maintain platform stability through compression and direction change. Fuel consumption among highest of season due to extended full-throttle periods. Tire warm-up challenging in cool Ardennes conditions.	02:02.768	4	2024-01-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	circuit-de-spa-francorchamps	2026-04-10 11:29:26.534+05:30	2026-04-09 19:10:57.887+05:30
4	Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya	barcelona	CAT	BCN	The Complete Test of Machine and Driver	World-class permanent racing circuit located in Montmeló, approximately 20 kilometers northeast of Barcelona, Spain. Opened in 1991 ahead of the 1992 Barcelona Olympic Games, the circuit has hosted the Spanish Formula 1 Grand Prix continuously since its inauguration and the Catalan MotoGP round since 1992. The layout is renowned within motorsport as one of the most comprehensive tests of vehicle performance, featuring a long main straight with heavy braking into Turn 1, the demanding Turn 3 right-hander that stresses right-front tires, the high-speed Turn 9 right-hander taken at over 240 km/h, and the technical final chicane complex. Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya serves as the primary winter testing venue for numerous international championships due to its balanced layout, consistent climate, and world-class facilities.	permanent	4.657	2.894	14	2	clockwise	1	29	140700	0101000020E610000082E2C798BB160240295C8FC2F5C84440	Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya\\nCarrer Mas Moreneta\\n08160 Montmeló\\nBarcelona, Spain	204	1991-09-10 17:00:00+05:30	2026-04-10 17:00:00+05:30	2	5	https://www.circuitcat.com	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Catalonia's Temple of Speed", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya emerged from the ambitious infrastructure development surrounding the 1992 Barcelona Olympic Games, opening its doors in September 1991 with immediate inclusion on the Formula 1 calendar. The circuit was designed to incorporate every type of corner a racing car might encounter—high-speed sweepers, heavy braking zones, technical combinations, and a kilometer-long straight—creating what engineers consider the definitive reference for vehicle performance evaluation.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The circuit has witnessed countless historic moments: Nigel Mansell and Ayrton Senna's wheel-to-wheel battle down the main straight in 1991, Michael Schumacher's remarkable victory in 1996 in torrential conditions that showcased his legendary wet-weather mastery, and Fernando Alonso's emotional home victories that ignited Spanish motorsport passion. The venue has hosted F1 pre-season testing for decades, with lap times at Barcelona becoming the unofficial benchmark by which championship prospects are measured.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "For AF Motorsport, Barcelona represents a critical venue on the Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica calendar. The circuit's demanding nature requires precise setup compromise between the high-speed demands of Turns 3 and 9 and the mechanical grip requirements of the final sector. Success at Barcelona validates both driver technique and engineering capability, making it a key performance indicator for the team's competitive standing.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Extensive runoff areas but track limits strictly enforced at Turns 1, 9, and final chicane. Paddock access requires advance credential registration. Garage allocation based on championship standing. Noise testing mandatory for all sessions.	02:02.768	4	2026-01-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	circuit-de-barcelona-catalunya	2026-04-10 11:29:46.095+05:30	2026-04-09 19:10:26.313+05:30
3	Circuito de Jerez - Ángel Nieto	jerez	JER	JER	Andalusian Speed Cathedral	Historic permanent racing circuit located near Jerez de la Frontera in southern Spain's Andalusia region. Opened in 1985 and renamed in 2018 to honor legendary Spanish motorcycle racer Ángel Nieto, the circuit has hosted the Spanish Motorcycle Grand Prix continuously since 1987 and the Spanish Formula 1 Grand Prix from 1986 to 1990 before the event moved to Barcelona. Jerez is characterized by its smooth, flowing layout featuring a mix of fast sweepers and tight, technical corners that reward precise car placement and smooth driving technique. The circuit's stadium section creates an amphitheater atmosphere unique in European motorsport.	permanent	4.428	2.751	13	1	clockwise	1	12	125000	0101000020E6100000DFE00B93A95A42404FAF9465882318C0	Carretera de Arcos, 11405 Jerez de la Frontera	172	1985-12-08 17:00:00+05:30	\N	4	6	https://www.circuitodejerez.com	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Andalusia's Racing Heritage", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Circuito de Jerez emerged during Spain's motorsport renaissance of the 1980s, hosting its first Formula 1 Grand Prix in 1986 with Ayrton Senna claiming victory by a mere 0.014 seconds over Nigel Mansell—one of the closest finishes in F1 history. The circuit quickly established itself as a favorite among drivers for its flowing nature and among fans for the unparalleled atmosphere created by the passionate Andalusian crowds.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Smooth surface with excellent grip characteristics. Track evolution significant throughout sessions. Final corner (Curva Ducados) requires commitment for strong exit onto main straight. Stadium section creates unique acoustics—driver can hear crowd reaction. Winter testing availability excellent with typically favorable weather.	01:38.051	3	2020-01-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	circuito-de-jerez---ngel-nieto	2026-04-10 11:30:04.985+05:30	2026-04-09 19:10:01.462+05:30
1	Autódromo Internacional do Algarve	portimao	ALG	POR	The Rollercoaster	Modern permanent racing circuit located near Portimão in Portugal's Algarve region, approximately 15 kilometers north of the coastal city. Opened in 2008, the circuit has rapidly established itself as one of Europe's most challenging and spectacular venues, characterized by dramatic elevation changes, blind crests, and a layout that demands absolute commitment from drivers. The circuit's signature undulating profile has earned it the nickname 'The Rollercoaster' among drivers and fans alike. Autódromo Internacional do Algarve has hosted MotoGP, FIA World Endurance Championship, Formula 1 (Portuguese Grand Prix return in 2020-2021), and numerous European championships. The venue is widely praised by competitors for its challenging yet rewarding nature and excellent safety standards	permanent	4.653	2.891	15	2	clockwise	1	32	100000	0101000020E610000012143FC6DC9D4240151DC9E53F4421C0	Autódromo Internacional do Algarve\\nSítio do Escampadinho\\nMexilhoeira Grande\\n8500-510 Portimão, Portugal	172	2008-11-02 17:00:00+05:30	2026-04-03 17:00:00+05:30	7	7	https://www.autodromodoalgarve.com	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Portugal's Modern Masterpiece", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Autódromo Internacional do Algarve represents Portugal's commitment to world-class motorsport infrastructure. Conceived as part of the Algarve's tourism development strategy, the circuit was designed by renowned architect Ricardo Pina to maximize the natural topography of the rolling Algarve hills, creating a layout that flows with the landscape rather than fighting against it.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The circuit's most distinctive features include the daunting descent into Turn 1 with heavy braking while the car is unsettled by the downhill slope, the blind crest approaching Turn 5 that requires absolute faith in reference points, and the spectacular drop through Turns 10 and 11 that compresses drivers into their seats before launching uphill toward the Galaxy straight. The layout demands a rare combination of bravery through blind high-speed sections and precision through the technical final sector.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "For AF Motorsport, Portimão holds special significance as one of Portugal's two premier international circuits. The team maintains strong relationships with circuit management and regularly conducts testing programs at the venue. Success at Portimão carries particular weight within Portuguese motorsport circles, and the circuit's challenging nature rewards the meticulous preparation that defines AF Motorsport's operational philosophy.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Circuit features significant elevation changes affecting aerodynamic performance and braking stability. Setup compromise required between high-speed crest stability and mechanical grip through final sector. Paddock facilities are excellent with individual garage units. Strong winds can affect car balance, particularly through exposed Turn 5-6 complex.	01:42.136	1	2023-01-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	autdromo-internacional-do-algarve	2026-04-10 11:31:02.144+05:30	2026-04-09 19:09:45.342+05:30
6	Circuito do Estoril - Kartódromo	estoril-kart	EST-K	EST-K	Portugal's Premier Karting Facility	CIK-FIA homologated international karting circuit located within the Autodromo do Estoril complex. The kartodromo features a challenging 1.2-kilometer layout designed specifically for competitive karting from entry-level to international championship standard. The circuit incorporates elevation changes, technical combinations, and high-speed sections that develop fundamental racing skills transferable to car racing. AF Motorsport utilizes this facility extensively for driver development programs, talent identification, and corporate partner activation events.	permanent	1.2	0.746	11	0	clockwise	1	8	2000	0101000020E6100000AA6054522760434000000000000024C0	Av. Alfredo César Torres, 2645-319 Alcabideche	172	1998-05-15 17:00:00+05:30	\N	4	5	https://www.circuito-estoril.pt/kartodromo	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Foundation of Portuguese Talent", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "For AF Motorsport, the kartódromo represents the foundation of the team's driver development philosophy. The facility is used extensively for fundamental skill development, with emphasis on racing line precision, brake and throttle modulation, and wheel-to-wheel race craft in a cost-effective environment. The proximity to the team's main workshop allows seamless integration between karting activities and car racing preparation.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	AF Motorsport conducts monthly driver assessment days at this facility. Track rental available for private testing and corporate events. Kart fleet maintained on-site for arrive-and-drive programs.	00:49.832	3	2022-01-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	circuito-do-estoril---kartdromo	2026-04-10 11:29:10.339+05:30	2026-04-09 19:12:15.318+05:30
2	Autódromo do Estoril	estoril	EST	EST	The Home of Portuguese Motorsport	Historic permanent racing circuit located in Estoril, Portugal, approximately 30 kilometers west of Lisbon. Originally opened in 1972, the circuit gained international prominence hosting the Portuguese Formula 1 Grand Prix from 1984 to 1996. The track is renowned for its challenging combination of high-speed corners, elevation changes, and technical sections that demand precise car setup and driver commitment. Autódromo do Estoril serves as the home circuit and operational headquarters for AF Motorsport, with team facilities located within the circuit complex. The venue regularly hosts major international championships including the FIM Superbike World Championship, FIA World Endurance Championship, and numerous European and Iberian series.	permanent	4.182	2.599	13	2	clockwise	2	27	45000	0101000020E61000001CEBE2361A604340992A1895D4C922C0	Av. Alfredo César Torres, 2645-319 Alcabideche	172	1972-06-17 17:00:00+05:30	\N	6	4	https://www.circuito-estoril.pt	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The Legacy of Estoril", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	AF Motorsport workshop located in Garage 12-14 complex, north paddock. Circuit noise restrictions apply 22:00-08:00 daily. Paddock access requires credential display at all times. Track rental available for private testing with 14-day advance booking requirement.	01:28.736	2	2023-01-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	autdromo-do-estoril	2026-04-10 11:30:35.171+05:30	2026-04-09 19:09:49.112+05:30
7	Rampa Porca de Murça	murca-hillclimb	MUR	RPM	Portugal's Premier Hillclimb Challenge	The Rampa Porca de Murça hillclimb course, located in northern Portugal's Vila Real district, represents one of the most challenging and prestigious hillclimb venues on the Iberian Peninsula. The demanding 5.2-kilometer asphalt ribbon climbs through picturesque Portuguese countryside, featuring a combination of high-speed straights, technical corners, blind crests, and significant elevation changes that test both driver commitment and vehicle setup.	temporary	5.2	3.231	35	0	clockwise	\N	180	8000	0101000020E6100000F9A067B3EAB344401B9E5E29CBD01DC0	 EN15, Murça, Vila Real District, Portugal	172	1990-05-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	2	4	https://www.rampaporcademurca.pt	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " The Rampa Porca de Murça has been a fixture of Portuguese hillclimb competition for over three decades, consistently attracting top national competitors and international entries. The event's challenging nature and spectacular setting in the Douro wine region have made it a favorite among drivers and fans alike.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The course record has fallen multiple times in recent years as machinery and driver standards continue to evolve. The 2025 edition saw particularly memorable competition, with AF Motorsport's reflection that \\"the road remembers what we did in 2025\\" capturing the emotional connection drivers develop with this demanding asphalt ribbon.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2026 edition marks AF Motorsport's expanded commitment to the event with a two-car Porsche entry, signaling the team's serious intentions in Portuguese hillclimb competition.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Hillclimb format with single-car timed runs at 30-second intervals. Event typically held in late March. Course features significant elevation gain of 180 meters from start to finish. Spectator access points designated along the route with shuttle service provided.	02:14.837	\N	2025-03-30 17:00:00+05:30	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	rampa-porca-de-mura	2026-04-10 15:57:55.736+05:30	2026-04-10 15:57:55.735+05:30
