COPY public.drivers (id, first_name, middle_name, last_name, alias, basics_racing_number, basics_nickname, basics_competition_name, basics_callsign, basics_catchphrase, basics_birth_date, basics_debut_date, basics_retirement_date, basics_nationality_id, basics_gender, basics_pronouns, details_story, details_biography, assets_avatar_id, assets_autograph_id, assets_cover_id, generate_slug, slug, updated_at, created_at) FROM stdin;
2	Tiago	Vagaroso	Monteiro	tiago-monteiro	18	Tiago	Tiago Monteiro	Monteiro	Experience teaches. Speed delivers.	1976-07-24 17:00:00+05:30	1997-03-15 17:00:00+05:30	\N	172	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Tiago Monteiro stands as Portugal's most accomplished international racing driver, with a career spanning the absolute pinnacle of motorsport and demonstrating remarkable versatility across Formula 1, World Touring Car Championship, and endurance racing. His journey from Portuguese Formula Ford novice to Formula 1 podium finisher, and subsequently to factory driver status in multiple world championships, represents the highest level of achievement ever attained by a Portuguese racing driver.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Monteiro's Formula 1 career, while brief by the standards of the sport's longest-serving drivers, included one of the most remarkable podium finishes in Formula 1 history. The 2005 United States Grand Prix, marred by tire safety concerns that limited the field to just six cars, saw Monteiro guide his Jordan-Toyota to third place—a result that, while achieved in extraordinary circumstances, required the same precise execution and mental focus as any other podium finish. His composed performance that day, maintaining concentration despite the surreal circumstances, demonstrated the professionalism that would characterize his entire career.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition from Formula 1 to touring car competition might have been viewed by some as a step backward, but Monteiro embraced the opportunity to compete for victories and championships rather than merely participating. His tenure in the World Touring Car Championship with SEAT and later Honda yielded multiple race victories, consistent championship contention, and established him as one of the category's most respected competitors. The factory Honda program provided the resources and support to compete at the highest level, and Monteiro delivered performances that justified that investment.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2017 WTCC season, where Monteiro was leading the championship before a testing accident resulted in serious injuries that sidelined him for the remainder of the campaign, demonstrated both his competitive peak and his extraordinary resilience. The recovery process—physical, mental, and emotional—tested him in ways that racing never had. His eventual return to competition, while the championship landscape had shifted during his absence, spoke volumes about his character and determination.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Beyond his competitive achievements, Monteiro has embraced a broader role within motorsport as mentor, ambassador, and advocate for Portuguese racing talent. His relationship with AF Motorsport and André Fernandes represents a natural alignment of values and a shared commitment to elevating Portuguese motorsport standards. Monteiro's experience across motorsport's highest categories provides invaluable perspective for strategic decision-making, driver development, and navigating the complex commercial and competitive landscape of professional racing.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Monteiro's continued involvement in GT and endurance racing, including appearances at the 24 Hours of Le Mans and major international events, demonstrates that his competitive fire remains undiminished. His ability to remain relevant and competitive across multiple decades and categories speaks to fundamental qualities—adaptability, intelligence, and pure driving talent—that transcend any specific era or formula.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Early Years and Portuguese Foundation (1989-1997):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Tiago Monteiro was born in Porto, Portugal's northern commercial capital, into a family with no significant motorsport background. His interest in racing developed through exposure to Formula 1 broadcasts and a natural affinity for speed and competition. Unlike many of his contemporaries who began karting in early childhood, Monteiro's competitive motorsport journey began relatively late at age fifteen through the Portuguese Formula Ford championship.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The late start, rather than proving a disadvantage, may have contributed to Monteiro's methodical approach to career development. Without the extensive karting background that many drivers rely upon for fundamental skills, he was forced to accelerate his learning curve and develop efficient techniques for acquiring new capabilities. This adaptability would prove essential throughout a career that demanded transitions between vastly different racing disciplines.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Success in Portuguese Formula Ford came quickly, with race victories and championship contention demonstrating natural talent. Progression through French Formula 3 and Formula Renault provided exposure to increasingly competitive European fields and the professional standards required at higher levels. Results were consistently solid, though not spectacular enough to attract the attention of major Formula 1 teams' junior programs.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The critical breakthrough came through performance in International Formula 3000, then the primary feeder series for Formula 1. Competing against fields packed with manufacturer-supported young drivers, Monteiro's performances demonstrated that he could compete at the level required for Formula 1 consideration. The opportunity with Jordan Grand Prix for the 2005 season represented validation of years of persistent effort and strategic career management.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Formula 1 Career and Historic Achievement (2005-2006):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Monteiro's Formula 1 debut with Jordan Grand Prix in 2005 placed him in one of the most challenging situations on the grid. Jordan, once a race-winning team, had entered a period of decline with limited resources and an uncompetitive chassis-engine package. The realistic objective for the season was not points or podiums but simply demonstrating professionalism and extracting whatever performance the car possessed.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2005 United States Grand Prix at Indianapolis Motor Speedway produced one of Formula 1's most controversial and unusual races. Tire safety concerns following failures during practice sessions led Michelin to advise its partner teams—comprising fourteen of the twenty cars entered—against racing. The resulting six-car field, consisting solely of Bridgestone-shod cars including Monteiro's Jordan, created a scenario unprecedented in Formula 1 history.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Amid the controversy and confusion, Monteiro maintained professional focus and executed his race with the same precision he would have applied to any grand prix. His third-place finish, securing Jordan's final Formula 1 podium, stands in the record books alongside any other achievement in the sport's history. More importantly, his composed handling of the extraordinary circumstances demonstrated the mental fortitude that defines professional racing drivers.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2005 season also yielded an eighth-place finish at the Belgian Grand Prix—securing a championship point in a full-field race—and consistent performances that outperformed the car's capabilities. When Jordan transitioned to Midland F1 for 2006, Monteiro remained with the team, continuing to demonstrate his value despite increasingly difficult circumstances. The Midland team's eventual sale to Spyker and subsequent restructuring ended Monteiro's Formula 1 tenure, but his performances had established a professional reputation that would serve him well in subsequent career phases.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    World Touring Car Championship Success (2007-2017):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition to the World Touring Car Championship with SEAT Sport represented a strategic career pivot that would define Monteiro's most successful competitive period. The WTCC provided an environment where driver talent could more directly influence outcomes, without the overwhelming performance disparities that characterize Formula 1. SEAT's factory program offered competitive equipment and professional support, creating conditions where Monteiro could demonstrate his full capabilities.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The learning curve in touring car competition was steep. The front-wheel-drive SEAT León required fundamentally different driving techniques than the formula cars Monteiro had campaigned throughout his career. Weight transfer management, tire preservation across longer races, and the physical nature of touring car competition demanded adaptation. Characteristically, Monteiro approached this transition with methodical analysis and unwavering work ethic.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Results improved steadily through his initial SEAT seasons, with podium finishes becoming increasingly frequent. A move to the factory Honda program for 2012 elevated Monteiro to championship-contending status. The Honda Civic WTCC provided a competitive platform, and Monteiro's experience and technical feedback contributed significantly to the car's continuous development.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2017 season represented Monteiro at his competitive peak. Leading the championship entering the summer break, he had established himself as the driver to beat in the world's premier touring car championship. A testing accident in September, resulting in serious head and neck injuries, ended his championship campaign and threatened his career. The recovery process—spanning months of rehabilitation, uncertainty, and gradual return to fitness—tested Monteiro's resilience as nothing before had.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    His eventual return to competition, while the WTCC had evolved into the WTCR (World Touring Car Cup) during his absence, demonstrated extraordinary determination. Results following his return never quite reached the heights of his pre-accident form, but the mere fact of his comeback represented victory in its own right.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Endurance Racing and Current Programs (2018-Present):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Monteiro's post-WTCC career has embraced the diverse opportunities of modern motorsport. Endurance racing appearances, including the 24 Hours of Le Mans and major GT events, have demonstrated his adaptability and enduring competitiveness. His technical feedback and experience make him a valued addition to any driver lineup, particularly in endurance formats where consistency and reliability often outweigh outright single-lap pace.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The relationship with AF Motorsport represents a natural evolution of Monteiro's commitment to Portuguese motorsport development. His role as strategic advisor and mentor leverages decades of experience across motorsport's highest categories to benefit the next generation of Portuguese talent. His presence within the AF Motorsport ecosystem provides validation of the team's professional standards and development philosophy.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Monteiro's broader ambassadorial activities—representing Portuguese motorsport at international events, engaging with media and commercial partners, and inspiring young drivers—demonstrate his understanding that a racing driver's legacy extends beyond statistics. He has embraced the responsibility that accompanies his status as Portugal's most accomplished international driver, using his platform to advocate for the sport's growth and development within his home country.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	f	tiago-monteiro	2026-04-10 11:15:19.724+05:30	2026-04-09 20:34:46.817+05:30
3	Pedro	Mourão	Lamy	pedro-lamy	7	Lamy	Pedro Lamy	Lamy	Speed never ages. Wisdom never fades.	1972-03-20 17:00:00+05:30	1989-05-10 17:00:00+05:30	2026-04-08 17:00:00+05:30	172	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Pedro Lamy's extraordinary career spans over three decades at motorsport's absolute highest levels, from Formula 1 with Lotus and Minardi to factory GT programs with Aston Martin, Mercedes-Benz, and Peugeot. His longevity and consistent competitiveness across multiple eras and categories represent an achievement unique in Portuguese motorsport and exceptionally rare in international racing.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The early promise demonstrated through victory at the prestigious Marlboro Masters of Formula 3 at Zandvoort in 1992—defeating a field that included future Formula 1 stars—established Lamy as one of Europe's most exciting young talents. His graduation to Formula 1 with Lotus came with the weight of expectation that accompanies such early success. A points finish in his debut race at the 1993 Italian Grand Prix, achieved in difficult circumstances with the underfunded Lotus team, demonstrated that the promise was genuine.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    A catastrophic testing accident at Silverstone in 1994, resulting in severe leg injuries that required extensive rehabilitation, interrupted Lamy's Formula 1 trajectory at a critical moment. The recovery process demanded extraordinary physical and mental determination, and his eventual return to competition with Minardi represented victory in itself. While the Formula 1 career that followed never quite reached the heights that early promise suggested, Lamy's performances in uncompetitive machinery consistently earned respect throughout the paddock.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition to sportscar and GT racing marked the beginning of Lamy's most successful and enduring competitive phase. Factory programs with Aston Martin, where he contributed significantly to the development of the DBR9 program, Mercedes-Benz in DTM and GT competition, and Peugeot's factory endurance effort provided the competitive equipment his talent deserved. Victories at the 24 Hours of Nürburgring, class wins at Le Mans, and championship success across multiple series demonstrated his extraordinary adaptability and technical intelligence.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Lamy's value to manufacturer programs extends far beyond his driving. His technical feedback, development capability, and methodical approach to performance optimization have made him one of the most respected development drivers in endurance racing. The ability to translate complex vehicle behavior into clear, actionable feedback for engineers—a skill honed through decades of experience across diverse machinery—makes Lamy an invaluable asset to any technical program.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    As the elder statesman of Portuguese motorsport, Lamy's perspective and experience provide invaluable guidance for AF Motorsport's strategic direction and driver development philosophy. His continued competitive involvement, including historic racing appearances and selected modern GT events, demonstrates that the fundamental skills that made him a Formula 3 champion remain intact. Pedro Lamy embodies the principle that true racing talent, combined with intelligence and professionalism, transcends age and category boundaries.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Early Years and Meteoric Rise (1985-1992):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    José Pedro Mourão Lamy Viçoso was born in Alenquer, Portugal, into a family with modest means but significant motorsport enthusiasm. His introduction to competitive driving came through karting, where natural talent was immediately evident despite limited resources compared to many competitors. Success in Portuguese national karting championships provided the foundation for progression to car racing.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition to Portuguese Formula Ford demonstrated that Lamy's talent translated effectively from karts to cars. Race victories and championship contention attracted attention from established European teams, leading to opportunities in British Formula Ford—then the world's most competitive junior formula category. Success in this environment, competing against drivers with significantly greater resources and experience, marked Lamy as a driver of exceptional potential.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Progression to Formula 3 with the crack West Surrey Racing team placed Lamy in the ideal environment to demonstrate his capabilities. The 1992 season culminated in victory at the Marlboro Masters of Formula 3 at Zandvoort, defeating a field that included future Formula 1 race winners and champions. This single result transformed Lamy's career trajectory, elevating him from promising regional talent to one of Europe's most sought-after young drivers.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Formula 1 Promise and Adversity (1993-1996):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The Formula 1 debut with Lotus in 1993 came with significant pressure and expectation. Lotus, once the sport's most innovative and successful team, had entered a period of decline that would ultimately prove terminal. Despite the challenging circumstances, Lamy scored a championship point in his debut race at the Italian Grand Prix—a remarkable achievement given the car's limitations and his inexperience at Formula 1 level.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 1994 season brought tragedy and adversity in equal measure. A horrific testing accident at Silverstone in May resulted in severe leg injuries that threatened not only his career but his ability to walk normally. The subsequent recovery required multiple surgeries, months of intensive rehabilitation, and extraordinary mental determination. Lamy's return to Formula 1 with Minardi for the 1995 season represented a triumph of will over circumstance.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The Minardi years demonstrated Lamy's professionalism and resilience. Driving equipment that was fundamentally uncompetitive, he consistently maximized whatever performance was available while maintaining positive relationships within the team. A brief return to a race seat in 1996 following Giancarlo Fisichella's departure provided opportunity to remind the paddock of his capabilities, but the Formula 1 landscape had shifted during his recovery period.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Sportscar Renaissance and Factory Driver Status (1997-2010):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition to sportscar and GT racing marked the beginning of Lamy's most successful and sustained competitive period. A relationship with Aston Martin Racing, beginning with the development of the DBR9 program, provided opportunity to demonstrate the technical intelligence and development capability that would become his trademark. Lamy's feedback was instrumental in refining the DBR9 into a Le Mans class winner and championship-winning platform.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Factory status with Mercedes-Benz followed, encompassing DTM competition and GT programs. The Mercedes relationship demonstrated Lamy's versatility across different vehicle types and competition formats. His ability to adapt driving technique to diverse machinery—front-engine GT cars, high-downforce prototypes, production-based touring cars—made him uniquely valuable to manufacturer programs seeking drivers who could contribute across multiple platforms.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The Peugeot factory endurance program provided Lamy's most sustained opportunity at the highest level of sportscar competition. Competing in the Le Mans Series and at the 24 Hours of Le Mans with the diesel-powered Peugeot 908, Lamy challenged for overall victories against Audi's dominant program. While ultimate Le Mans victory proved elusive, his contributions to Peugeot's championship success and his consistent performances in endurance racing's most demanding events cemented his reputation.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Victories at the 24 Hours of Nürburgring—widely considered the world's most demanding endurance race—represented career highlights. The combination of a challenging circuit, unpredictable weather, and intense competition creates conditions that reward experience, intelligence, and adaptability. Lamy's success at the Nürburgring demonstrated that these qualities, rather than raw single-lap pace, defined his competitive value.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Continuing Legacy and Mentorship (2011-Present):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    As competitive opportunities at the highest levels of modern motorsport have evolved, Lamy has embraced roles that leverage his extraordinary experience. Historic racing appearances in significant machinery from his career provide connection to motorsport heritage while demonstrating that his fundamental driving skills remain intact. Selected appearances in contemporary GT events confirm that age has not diminished his competitive capability.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Lamy's advisory relationship with AF Motorsport represents a natural evolution of his commitment to Portuguese motorsport development. His perspective—shaped by experience at the absolute pinnacle of the sport across multiple eras—provides invaluable context for strategic decision-making. His understanding of what truly drives performance, developed through decades of hands-on engagement with diverse machinery and technical programs, informs AF Motorsport's approach to driver development and technical preparation.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Perhaps Lamy's most significant contribution to Portuguese motorsport extends beyond any specific result or championship. His career demonstrates that Portuguese drivers can compete successfully at the highest international levels when talent is combined with intelligence, professionalism, and unwavering determination. This example has inspired generations of Portuguese racing talent, including those now developing within AF Motorsport's programs.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Pedro Lamy embodies a set of values that transcend specific competitive achievements: resilience in the face of adversity, continuous adaptation to changing circumstances, and the understanding that true professionalism encompasses far more than speed alone. These qualities, rather than any single result, define his legacy within Portuguese and international motorsport.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	f	pedro-lamy	2026-04-10 11:16:38.844+05:30	2026-04-09 20:41:13.077+05:30
4	António 	Félix da	Costa	antonio-felix-da-costa	13	Da Costa	António Félix da Costa	Da Costa	Electric speed. Portuguese pride.	1991-08-31 17:00:00+05:30	2008-03-20 17:00:00+05:30	2026-04-16 17:00:00+05:30	172	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " António Félix da Costa represents the modern evolution of Portuguese motorsport talent, achieving championship success in Formula E while maintaining strong connections to his Portuguese roots and the development pathway that shaped his career. His journey from Red Bull Junior Team prospect to Formula E World Champion demonstrates resilience, adaptability, and the importance of finding the right competitive environment.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The early career trajectory suggested Formula 1 as the natural destination. Victory at the prestigious Macau Grand Prix in 2012, success in Formula Renault and Formula 3, and association with the Red Bull Junior Team positioned da Costa as one of Europe's most promising young drivers. When the anticipated Formula 1 opportunity failed to materialize—a familiar story for countless talented drivers—da Costa faced the critical career decision that defines so many motorsport journeys: persist in pursuit of a narrowing pathway or pivot toward emerging opportunities.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition to touring car competition with BMW and the burgeoning Formula E championship represented that strategic pivot. Initial results in Formula E were promising rather than spectacular, with flashes of pace offset by inconsistency. The championship-winning 2019-2020 season with DS Techeetah represented the culmination of accumulated experience, technical understanding, and the perfect alignment of driver, team, and equipment. The title validated da Costa's decision to embrace electric racing's premier championship and established him among the discipline's elite competitors.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Da Costa's continued involvement with Porsche—competing in Formula E with the TAG Heuer Porsche Formula E Team and in the World Endurance Championship with the Porsche 963 Hypercar program—demonstrates his versatility and enduring competitiveness. The relationship with Porsche creates natural connection to AF Motorsport's Porsche-focused program, with shared manufacturer affiliation and complementary development philosophies.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The connection between da Costa and AF Motorsport centers on shared Portuguese motorsport heritage and the importance of structured development pathways. His career demonstrates the possibilities available to Portuguese drivers who combine talent with professional preparation, strategic career management, and the adaptability to embrace emerging opportunities. As an inspiration for Portuguese motorsport's next generation, da Costa's journey validates AF Motorsport's emphasis on developing complete racing professionals prepared for the diverse opportunities of modern motorsport.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Early Years and Portuguese Foundation (1999-2007):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    António Félix da Costa was born in Lisbon, Portugal, into a family with modest motorsport background. His introduction to competitive driving came through karting at age eight, competing initially in Portuguese national championships. Success came quickly, with multiple national titles demonstrating natural talent and competitive instinct.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition from Portuguese karting to European competition represented the first major step in da Costa's development. Competing against the best young drivers from across Europe provided both challenge and opportunity. Results at European level were competitive, attracting attention from talent scouts and establishing da Costa within the international junior motorsport community.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    European Single-Seater Progression (2008-2013):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition to car racing came through Formula Renault, first in the Portuguese championship and subsequently in the highly competitive Northern European Cup. The learning curve was steep, with initial results modest as da Costa adapted to the demands of formula car competition. Consistent improvement through his first full seasons demonstrated the capacity for development that would characterize his career.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    A breakthrough came in 2012 with victory at the Macau Grand Prix—the most prestigious Formula 3 event in the world. Success at Macau requires a unique combination of bravery, precision, and adaptability to the challenging street circuit. Da Costa's victory placed him alongside previous winners including Ayrton Senna, Michael Schumacher, and David Coulthard—a lineage that immediately elevated his profile within the motorsport community.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Association with the Red Bull Junior Team provided resources, opportunity, and the pressure that accompanies manufacturer backing. Success in Formula Renault 3.5, then the primary feeder series for Formula 1, positioned da Costa as a legitimate Formula 1 prospect. When anticipated opportunities failed to materialize—the familiar story of timing, politics, and circumstance that defines so many promising careers—da Costa faced the critical decision point that would define his professional trajectory.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Transition and Reinvention (2014-2018):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition to DTM with BMW represented a significant career pivot. The German touring car championship demands a different skill set than single-seaters—heavier cars, different tire characteristics, and intensely physical competition. The learning curve was substantial, and results during the DTM years were inconsistent. Yet this period proved formative, broadening da Costa's driving repertoire and developing the adaptability that would serve him well in subsequent career phases.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Simultaneous involvement with the emerging Formula E championship provided exposure to electric racing's unique demands. Energy management, strategic efficiency, and the distinctive characteristics of temporary street circuits required different approaches than traditional racing formats. Da Costa's methodical approach to understanding these demands—characteristic of his development throughout his career—laid groundwork for future success.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The BMW relationship, while not yielding the results either party had hoped for in DTM, provided stability and professional development during a critical career phase. When the opportunity to join DS Techeetah in Formula E emerged for the 2019-2020 season, da Costa was prepared to maximize the opportunity.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Formula E World Champion (2019-2020):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2019-2020 Formula E season represented the culmination of da Costa's accumulated experience and the perfect alignment of driver, team, and equipment. The DS Techeetah package was the class of the field, and da Costa's performances extracted maximum value from that advantage. Three race victories and consistent podium finishes secured the championship in dominant fashion, validating the career decisions that had brought him to this point.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The championship transformed da Costa's career trajectory. From talented prospect whose Formula 1 opportunity had failed to materialize, he became a recognized champion in motorsport's fastest-growing category. The title opened doors to manufacturer programs, commercial opportunities, and the recognition that his talent had always deserved.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Porsche Era and Current Programs (2021-Present):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The relationship with Porsche—encompassing Formula E competition with the TAG Heuer Porsche Formula E Team and World Endurance Championship appearances with the Porsche 963 Hypercar—represents da Costa's current competitive phase. The Porsche affiliation provides access to one of motorsport's most prestigious manufacturer programs and creates natural connection to AF Motorsport's Porsche-focused activities.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Results in Formula E with Porsche have maintained da Costa's status among the championship's elite competitors, with race victories and consistent points-scoring performances. The Hypercar program in WEC provides opportunity to compete for overall victory at the 24 Hours of Le Mans and in the World Endurance Championship—ambitions that add significant chapters to an already distinguished career.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Da Costa's continued connection to Portuguese motorsport, including his relationship with AF Motorsport, reflects his understanding of the responsibility that accompanies his status as Portugal's most prominent active international driver. His example demonstrates to emerging Portuguese talent that success at the highest levels is achievable when talent combines with strategic career management, professional preparation, and the adaptability to embrace opportunity in whatever form it appears.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	f	antonio-felix-da-costa	2026-04-10 11:17:44.958+05:30	2026-04-09 20:47:09.316+05:30
7	José	Carlos	Barros	jose-barros	88	Zé	José Barros	Barros	Precision and consistency win races.	1998-06-15 17:00:00+05:30	2018-03-10 17:00:00+05:30	\N	172	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "José Barros joins AF Motorsport for the 2026 GT Cup Europe campaign, bringing a reputation for consistent pace and clean racecraft developed through Portuguese national championships. His methodical approach to race weekends aligns perfectly with AF Motorsport's preparation-focused philosophy. The opening round at Portimão demonstrated his immediate competitiveness within the team structure.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Barros has spent the past three seasons competing in the Campeonato de Portugal de Velocidade, securing multiple class podiums and establishing himself as one of Portugal's most consistent GT drivers. His technical feedback and tire management skills have drawn praise from engineers throughout his career.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The step to international GT Cup Europe competition with AF Motorsport represents the natural progression for a driver who has methodically built his skills and experience. Barros approaches this opportunity with characteristic preparation and focus.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "José Barros began karting at age ten at the Bombarral karting circuit, progressing through regional championships before transitioning to car racing in Portuguese Formula Ford. His early career demonstrated solid if unspectacular results, but his dedication to understanding vehicle dynamics and setup drew attention from established GT teams.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The move to GT racing in 2020 unlocked Barros's potential. His smooth driving style and mechanical sympathy proved ideally suited to production-based machinery, and results improved steadily through his first two seasons. A breakout 2023 campaign yielded three class victories and second in the CPV championship standings.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Barros's reputation as a driver who extracts maximum performance while preserving equipment made him a natural fit for AF Motorsport's endurance and multi-driver programs. His ability to provide clear, technically informed feedback accelerates setup development and benefits the entire engineering team.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	f	jose-barros	2026-04-10 15:52:11.433+05:30	2026-04-10 14:51:02.722+05:30
1	André	Miguel	 Fernandes	andre-fernandes	27	AF	André Fernandes	Fernandes	Performance through preparation. Speed through precision.	1995-08-15 17:00:00+05:30	2012-04-10 17:00:00+05:30	\N	172	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "André Fernandes's motorsport journey embodies the principle that sustained success is built upon continuous improvement and unwavering dedication. From early karting experiences at the Estoril Kartódromo to competing at the forefront of Iberian Porsche competition, his career trajectory reflects methodical progression and a commitment to excellence that has become the hallmark of AF Motorsport's organizational philosophy.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition from successful national competitor to team principal and lead driver of AF Motorsport represents both personal ambition and a broader vision for Portuguese motorsport. Recognizing that individual driving talent alone was insufficient for sustained success at the professional level, André invested years in building the operational infrastructure, technical partnerships, and personnel development systems that would become the foundation of AF Motorsport. This dual-track development—simultaneously refining his craft behind the wheel while constructing a professional organization around him—demonstrates a strategic sophistication rare among driver-owners.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2025 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica campaign validated this comprehensive approach. Three victories, nine total podium finishes, and third place in the championship standings in the team's debut Porsche season provided tangible evidence that meticulous preparation and strategic thinking translate directly to competitive success. Beyond the statistics, the season established AF Motorsport's credibility within the Porsche Motorsport ecosystem, built lasting relationships with technical and commercial partners, and created a platform for continued growth and achievement.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    André's driving style reflects his methodical nature—precise rather than spectacular, consistent rather than mercurial. His technical understanding, developed through years of hands-on engagement with vehicle dynamics and data analysis, enables effective communication with engineers and rapid adaptation to varying circuit characteristics. This intellectual approach to driving complements his organizational leadership, creating a coherent philosophy that permeates every aspect of AF Motorsport's operations.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Looking forward, André's vision extends beyond personal competitive achievement. He sees AF Motorsport as a vehicle for elevating Portuguese motorsport standards, developing the next generation of Portuguese racing talent, and demonstrating that Iberian teams can compete successfully at the European level without the resources of manufacturer-backed programs. This commitment to broader impact, combined with unwavering competitive focus, defines André Fernandes as both a driver and a leader.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "  Early Years and Karting Foundation (2003-2011):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    André Fernandes was born in Lisbon, Portugal, and raised in the coastal community of Cascais, just minutes from the historic Autódromo do Estoril. His introduction to motorsport came through his father, a passionate amateur racer who recognized his son's natural affinity for speed and competition. At age eight, André began karting at the Estoril Kartódromo, the same circuit that had launched generations of Portuguese racing talent.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The early karting years were characterized by rapid progression and an unusual maturity in approach. While other young drivers focused solely on winning, André displayed a fascination with the mechanical aspects of the sport—constantly questioning his father and mechanics about setup changes, tire pressures, and the relationship between adjustments and on-track behavior. This technical curiosity would become a defining characteristic of his career.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Competitive success came steadily through the Portuguese national karting ranks. Multiple regional championships and consistent top-five finishes in national competition demonstrated natural talent, but equally important was the network of relationships built during these formative years. Fellow competitors, mechanics, and team owners from this period would later become collaborators, employees, and partners in the AF Motorsport venture.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Transition to Car Racing and Single-Seater Development (2012-2016):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition from karting to car racing came through Portuguese Formula Ford in 2012. The category provided an accessible entry point to single-seater competition, and André's adaptation was characteristically methodical. Rather than pursuing immediate results at the expense of proper technique development, he focused on building the fundamental skills—trail braking, throttle modulation, race craft—that would serve him throughout his career.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Progression through Portuguese Formula 3 and selected European Formula Renault events followed over the next several seasons. Results were solid rather than spectacular, with occasional podium finishes demonstrating potential while inconsistent performances highlighted areas requiring development. This period was crucial for André's evolution as a driver, forcing him to confront the reality that natural talent alone was insufficient for sustained success at higher levels.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The single-seater years also provided his first exposure to professional team operations beyond the family-supported efforts of karting. Observing how different organizations approached preparation, driver development, and commercial management planted seeds that would later germinate in the AF Motorsport structure. He noted which methodologies produced consistent results and which created dysfunction despite significant resources.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    GT and Touring Car Experience (2017-2021):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    A pivotal career shift came in 2017 with the transition to GT and touring car competition in the Campeonato de Portugal de Velocidade. The move from single-seaters to production-based machinery required significant adaptation—different braking techniques, weight transfer management, and the unique challenges of racing heavier, less aerodynamically dependent vehicles. The transition proved formative, broadening André's driving repertoire and deepening his understanding of vehicle dynamics across different platforms.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    This period also marked his first experience as a team leader rather than merely a driver. As the most experienced competitor within his entry, André naturally assumed responsibility for setup direction, strategy input, and mentoring less experienced teammates. The satisfaction derived from collective achievement—seeing a teammate succeed with guidance he had provided—planted the seed for what would become AF Motorsport's driver development focus.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Results during this phase included multiple class victories, consistent podium finishes, and growing recognition within Portuguese motorsport circles. More importantly, the relationships built with mechanics, engineers, and commercial partners during these years would form the nucleus of the AF Motorsport organization.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Founding AF Motorsport and Strategic Development (2020-2024):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The decision to establish AF Motorsport in 2020 represented the culmination of years of observation, planning, and relationship building. André recognized that continued progression required an organizational structure beyond the traditional driver-for-hire model. He envisioned a team built on specific principles: meticulous preparation standards, data-driven performance optimization, and a genuine commitment to developing people alongside results.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The early years of AF Motorsport were characterized by deliberate, methodical growth. Rather than overextending resources in pursuit of immediate high-profile results, André focused on establishing proper foundations—securing workshop space at Estoril, building relationships with technical partners, developing operational procedures, and carefully selecting personnel who shared the team's values. This patient approach sometimes frustrated those who urged faster expansion, but it ensured that each growth step was sustainable and built upon solid ground.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition to Porsche competition, initially through selected Carrera Cup appearances and then the full Sprint Challenge Ibérica commitment, represented the culmination of this developmental phase. The Porsche platform provided the ideal environment for AF Motorsport's philosophy—a spec chassis that rewarded preparation and driver development over budgetary advantage, a professional paddock with high standards, and a clear pathway for progression through Porsche's international motorsport pyramid.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    2025 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica Campaign:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2025 season represented AF Motorsport's full commitment to Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica competition and exceeded all reasonable expectations. The campaign yielded three race victories, nine total podium finishes, three fastest lap awards, and third place in the final championship standings. Beyond the statistics, the season demonstrated that AF Motorsport's preparation methodology and development philosophy could compete successfully against established Porsche specialists.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Highlights included the emotional maiden victory at the Estoril season opener—a result that validated years of preparation and sacrifice—and the championship-securing victory at the Estoril finale that delivered third place in the standings. Throughout the season, André demonstrated the consistency that had become his trademark, finishing every race and scoring points in all twelve championship rounds.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2025 campaign also showcased André's dual capability as both driver and team principal. His ability to compartmentalize—focusing entirely on driving duties during sessions while seamlessly transitioning to organizational leadership between them—proved essential to the team's success. This unique combination of roles, challenging as it may be, creates an integrated approach to competition that distinguishes AF Motorsport within the paddock.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Driving Philosophy and Leadership Approach:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    André Fernandes's driving philosophy emphasizes precision over aggression, consistency over occasional brilliance. His technique prioritizes smooth inputs, optimal car placement, and tire preservation—approaches that reward the methodical preparation central to AF Motorsport's identity. He is not the most spectacular driver in the field, but he is reliably among the most effective at extracting the maximum available performance from any given situation.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    As a leader, André has cultivated a team culture that values contribution over hierarchy, continuous improvement over complacency, and shared success over individual recognition. Mechanics, engineers, and support staff are genuinely empowered to contribute ideas and identify improvements. This collaborative environment, combined with clear standards and accountability, has proven highly effective in attracting and retaining quality personnel.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    André's communication style reflects his technical background—precise, analytical, and free from hyperbole. He provides clear direction while remaining open to alternative perspectives, creating an environment where honest assessment of performance is valued over comfortable narratives. This intellectual honesty, applied equally to self-evaluation and team performance, accelerates the learning and improvement that defines AF Motorsport's trajectory.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	92	f	andr-fernandes	2026-04-25 18:04:51.51+05:30	2026-04-09 20:28:40.518+05:30
5	Felipe	Mas	sa	felipe-massa	19	Felipinho	Felipe Massa	Massa	Never give up. Always believe.	1981-04-25 17:00:00+05:30	1998-05-10 17:00:00+05:30	2017-11-26 17:00:00+05:30	30	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Felipe Massa's motorsport journey represents one of Formula 1's most compelling narratives of talent, resilience, and unwavering determination. From his early days karting in São Paulo to standing on the precipice of a Formula 1 World Championship, Massa's career embodies the passion and fighting spirit characteristic of Brazilian racing legends.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 2008 season defined Massa's legacy in the sport. Driving for Ferrari, he came within a single corner of winning the Formula 1 World Championship, crossing the finish line at his home Brazilian Grand Prix as the provisional champion, only for Lewis Hamilton to secure the necessary position at the final corner of the final lap. The grace and dignity Massa displayed in that devastating moment earned him universal respect and admiration throughout the motorsport world.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    A life-threatening accident during qualifying for the 2009 Hungarian Grand Prix, where a suspension spring from another car struck his helmet at high speed, nearly ended his career and his life. His remarkable recovery and return to Formula 1 competition demonstrated extraordinary physical and mental courage, further cementing his place in the hearts of racing fans worldwide.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Beyond his Formula 1 career spanning fifteen seasons with Sauber, Ferrari, and Williams, Massa has continued to compete at the highest levels of international motorsport including the FIA Formula E Championship and the Porsche Carrera Cup Brasil. His connection to AF Motorsport comes through shared Brazilian-Portuguese heritage, the Porsche competition pathway, and a mutual commitment to developing the next generation of racing talent.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Felipe Massa was born in São Paulo, Brazil, into a family with deep motorsport roots. He began karting at age eight, following in the footsteps of his father and uncle who were both accomplished racers. His natural talent was evident from the earliest days, winning numerous regional and national karting championships throughout his formative years.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Massa's transition to car racing came through Brazilian Formula Chevrolet in 1998, where he finished fifth in the championship as a rookie. The following year he claimed the title with dominant performances that attracted attention from European talent scouts. His progression through Formula Renault Eurocup and Formula 3000 demonstrated consistent front-running pace and earned him a Formula 1 test with Sauber.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Formula 1 Career Highlights (2002-2017):", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Sauber Years (2002, 2004-2005): Massa made his Formula 1 debut with Sauber in 2002 before a year as Ferrari test driver in 2003—an experience that proved formative for his development. Returning to Sauber for 2004-2005, he consistently outperformed the car's capabilities, catching Ferrari's attention.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Ferrari Years (2006-2013): Massa's dream move to Ferrari alongside Michael Schumacher in 2006 marked the pinnacle of his career. He secured his first pole position at the Turkish Grand Prix and his maiden victory at the same circuit, famously received over team radio with the words \\"Felipe baby, stay cool!\\" from his engineer Rob Smedley. The 2008 season saw Massa win six races and come within moments of the World Championship. The 2009 Hungarian Grand Prix accident and subsequent recovery demonstrated his extraordinary resilience. He remained with Ferrari through 2013, securing eleven total victories with the Scuderia.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Williams Years (2014-2017): Massa's final Formula 1 chapter with Williams Racing saw him achieve pole position at the 2014 Austrian Grand Prix and multiple podium finishes, demonstrating that his pace remained undiminished. His emotional farewell at the 2016 Brazilian Grand Prix—and subsequent return for 2017 when Valtteri Bottas departed—cemented his status as one of Formula 1's most beloved figures.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Post-Formula 1 Career:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Following his Formula 1 retirement, Massa competed in the FIA Formula E Championship with Venturi Racing, securing a podium finish in only his third ePrix start. He later transitioned to the Brazilian Stock Car Pro Series and Porsche Carrera Cup Brasil, continuing to demonstrate competitive pace while mentoring emerging Brazilian talent.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Felipe Massa's legacy extends beyond statistics. His sportsmanship, resilience, and genuine warmth have made him an ambassador for motorsport values worldwide. His connection to the AF Motorsport philosophy—emphasizing preparation, perseverance, and the development of complete racing professionals—makes him a natural inspiration for the organization.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	87	\N	\N	f	felipe-massa	2026-04-11 20:29:49.21+05:30	2026-04-10 10:48:53.678+05:30
6	Pipo	Felipe	Massa	pipo-massa	19	Pipo	Pipo Massa	Pipo	Racing is in my blood. Speed is my inheritance.	2010-11-30 17:00:00+05:30	2018-03-15 17:00:00+05:30	2026-04-07 17:00:00+05:30	30	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Pipo Massa carries forward one of motorsport's most cherished family legacies as the son of Formula 1 vice-champion Felipe Massa. Born into racing royalty, Pipo has embraced his heritage while forging his own identity on the track, demonstrating that talent, when combined with dedicated nurturing, can transcend generations.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Unlike many second-generation drivers who shy from the weight of their family name, Pipo has embraced the Massa legacy with maturity beyond his years. His approach combines the natural feel and car control inherited from his father with a modern understanding of data analysis, simulator training, and professional preparation that defines contemporary driver development.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Pipo's connection to AF Motorsport represents a natural alignment of values and vision. The team's emphasis on structured driver development, technical education, and professional conduct mirrors the environment in which he has been raised. His presence within AF Motorsport's junior programs brings international attention and validation to the organization's driver development philosophy while providing Pipo with the European racing exposure essential for career progression.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Pipo Massa was born in São Paulo, Brazil, into a family where motorsport is not merely a profession but a fundamental part of identity. His father Felipe was competing at the highest levels of Formula 1 throughout Pipo's early childhood, immersing him in the paddock environment from his earliest memories.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Karting Career:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Pipo began karting at age seven, following the traditional Brazilian pathway to motorsport excellence. His early results demonstrated that the Massa racing instinct had successfully transferred to the next generation, with multiple podium finishes in Brazilian national karting championships. His driving style shows clear paternal influence—smooth inputs, precise car placement, and exceptional feel for tire management—while incorporating modern techniques refined through contemporary coaching methodologies.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Junior Development:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    As Pipo progressed through the karting ranks, his development program was carefully structured to balance competitive experience with technical education. Unlike many young drivers who focus exclusively on seat time, Pipo's preparation has included comprehensive data analysis training, simulator work, physical conditioning, and media preparation—a holistic approach that aligns perfectly with AF Motorsport's driver development philosophy.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The transition from karting to car racing represents the critical phase in Pipo's young career. His first car racing experiences in Brazilian Formula 1600 demonstrated immediate competitiveness, with the smooth technique developed in karts translating effectively to formula car dynamics. His progression is being carefully managed to ensure each step provides appropriate challenge while building the technical foundation necessary for sustained success.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Connection to AF Motorsport:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Pipo's relationship with AF Motorsport developed through the shared Brazilian-Portuguese motorsport community and the natural alignment between the Massa family's values and the team's development philosophy. The opportunity to gain European racing experience within a structured, professionally managed environment provides Pipo with an ideal platform for the next phase of his career development.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    AF Motorsport's Porsche-focused program offers Pipo exposure to GT racing dynamics—an essential skill set for modern professional drivers who must demonstrate versatility across multiple categories. The team's data-driven approach to performance optimization complements the technical education Pipo has received throughout his development.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Long-term Vision:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    While the ultimate aspiration of any young driver with Formula 1 heritage is to reach the pinnacle of the sport, Pipo's development pathway is deliberately focused on building complete racing capability rather than rushing toward any specific destination. The combination of Brazilian racing passion with European professional structure—exactly the environment AF Motorsport provides—creates optimal conditions for Pipo to realize his considerable potential.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Whether his future lies in single-seaters, GT racing, or the increasingly blurred lines between categories, Pipo Massa represents the evolution of a racing dynasty. His journey embodies the AF Motorsport belief that sustained success is built upon preparation, education, and the development of complete racing professionals.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	f	pipo-massa	2026-04-10 10:58:28.883+05:30	2026-04-10 10:54:28.251+05:30
11	Rogério	Augusto	Grotta	rogerio-grotta	33	Grotta	Rogério Grotta	Grotta	Adapt and overcome	1992-07-19 17:00:00+05:30	2015-03-10 17:00:00+05:30	\N	30	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Rogério Grotta made an extraordinary AF Motorsport debut at Portimão, competing in the Porsche 991.2 GT3 R for the first time at a circuit he had never previously driven—in wet conditions. His remarkable performance included consistent pace, excellent car control, and fastest lap of the race, demonstrating exceptional adaptability and natural talent.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Grotta's Brazilian racing background encompasses diverse machinery across South American GT and endurance championships. His ability to quickly adapt to new cars, circuits, and conditions makes him a valuable addition to AF Motorsport's driver roster.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The Portimão performance suggests significant potential for continued success in European competition. Grotta's technical feedback and collaborative approach have already earned respect from AF Motorsport's engineering team.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Rogério Grotta's motorsport journey began in Brazilian karting before progressing through national formula car categories. His smooth driving style and mechanical sympathy proved particularly effective in GT machinery, leading to opportunities in South American endurance championships.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Success in Brazilian GT competition, including class victories at Interlagos and Curitiba, established Grotta as a consistent front-runner. His reputation for extracting performance in challenging conditions—rain, traffic, deteriorating tires—made him a sought-after endurance specialist.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The opportunity with AF Motorsport represents Grotta's European debut and a significant step in his international career. His Portimão performance, delivering fastest lap in his first GT3 R drive at an unfamiliar circuit in wet conditions, suggests the European paddock will see much more of this adaptable Brazilian talent.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	f	rogerio-grotta	2026-04-10 15:51:51.069+05:30	2026-04-10 15:51:51.069+05:30
8	Angelo	Marco	Fontana	angelo-fontana	55	Angelo	Angelo Fontana	Fontana	Fast, focused, fearless.	1994-09-22 17:00:00+05:30	2012-04-05 17:00:00+05:30	\N	104	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Angelo Fontana brings Italian racing passion and extensive European GT experience to AF Motorsport's expanded 2026 program. Competing in both International GT Open and Winter Series events, Fontana has demonstrated immediate pace and strong technical feedback. His partnership with André Fernandes in endurance formats provides a potent combination of experience and speed.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Fontana's career spans Italian GT championships, selected European endurance events, and factory-supported programs with Lamborghini and Audi. His smooth driving style and tire management expertise make him particularly effective in longer race formats where consistency often trumps outright aggression.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Joining AF Motorsport for 2026 provides Fontana with a professional environment to pursue championship ambitions across multiple series while contributing his experience to the team's development.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Angelo Fontana emerged from the competitive Italian karting scene, securing multiple national championships before transitioning to formula cars. Success in Italian Formula 3 opened doors to GT racing, where his adaptable driving style and technical acumen found their natural home.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    A factory-supported period with Lamborghini's Super Trofeo program yielded multiple race victories and valuable experience in international competition. Subsequent campaigns in Italian GT with Audi machinery demonstrated Fontana's ability to extract performance from diverse platforms.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Fontana's move to Porsche competition with AF Motorsport represents both a new challenge and an opportunity to apply accumulated experience in one of motorsport's most professional environments. His mentorship of younger teammates and collaborative approach to setup development have already made significant contributions to the team's progress.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	f	angelo-fontana	2026-04-10 15:52:35.136+05:30	2026-04-10 14:57:13.152+05:30
9	Leonardo	Filipe	Reis	leonardo-reis	42	Leo	Leonardo Reis	Reis	Every lap is an opportunity.	2000-11-08 17:00:00+05:30	2019-05-15 17:00:00+05:30	\N	172	Male	he/him	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Leonardo Reis steps up to GT Cup Europe competition with AF Motorsport for 2026, following successful campaigns in Portuguese national categories. His technical understanding and methodical approach to performance development complement the team's engineering-focused methodology. The Portimão season opener marked his international debut.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Reis represents the next generation of Portuguese racing talent, combining natural speed with an analytical approach unusual for his age. His willingness to engage deeply with data and setup development has accelerated his learning curve and earned respect from AF Motorsport's engineering team.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The GT Cup Europe campaign provides Reis with the international exposure and competitive seasoning essential for continued progression. His long-term potential suggests a bright future within the AF Motorsport driver development pathway.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Leonardo Reis began karting at age eight, progressing rapidly through Portuguese national categories. His smooth, precise driving style and exceptional car control drew attention from established teams, leading to opportunities in Portuguese Formula Ford and touring car categories.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    A formative season in the CPV championship demonstrated Reis's adaptability across different machinery and his capacity for rapid learning. His technical feedback impressed engineers and his consistent pace against more experienced competitors marked him as a driver with significant potential.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The step to international GT Cup Europe competition with AF Motorsport represents the logical next phase in Reis's development. The team's structured approach to driver progression and emphasis on technical education align perfectly with his learning style and career objectives.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	\N	f	leonardo-reis	2026-04-10 15:52:51.735+05:30	2026-04-10 15:12:38.565+05:30
10	Gabriela	Sofia	Correia	gabriela-correia	69	Princess of the Mountain	Gabriela Correia	Correia	Fearless on the mountain	1996-04-12 17:00:00+05:30	2014-03-20 17:00:00+05:30	\N	172	Female	she/her	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Gabriela Correia joins AF Motorsport for the 2026 Rampa Porca de Murça hillclimb, bringing extensive experience and a proven track record in Portuguese hillclimb competition. Known throughout the paddock as the \\"Princess of the Mountain,\\" her aggressive yet precise driving style has earned podiums and respect throughout the national hillclimb community.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Her debut with AF Motorsport in the Porsche 991.2 GT3 Cup demonstrated immediate pace despite challenging circumstances. An off-track moment that could have ended the weekend instead showcased the team's resilience, with mechanics executing a remarkable sub-30-minute repair that returned Correia to competition.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Correia's partnership with AF Motorsport combines her hillclimb expertise with factory-level Porsche support, creating a potent combination for the demanding Portuguese hillclimb calendar.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "  Gabriela Correia discovered her passion for motorsport through her father, a respected figure in Portuguese rallying. Her early exposure to mountain roads and rally stages shaped a driving style characterized by commitment, car control, and the unique bravery required for hillclimb competition.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Success came quickly in national hillclimb championships, with class victories and overall podiums establishing Correia as one of Portugal's most exciting female competitors. Her technical feedback and ability to extract maximum performance from diverse machinery attracted attention from teams and manufacturers.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Correia's \\"Princess of the Mountain\\" nickname reflects both her competitive achievements and her role inspiring the next generation of female motorsport participants. Her presence within AF Motorsport extends beyond driving to encompass mentorship and ambassadorial activities.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	91	f	gabriela-correia	2026-04-25 17:59:52.658+05:30	2026-04-10 15:23:59.525+05:30
\.


