4	Estoril Testing Off-Track Excursion 2025	estoril-test-off-track-2025	Minor off-track excursion during private testing at Autódromo do Estoril in preparation for the 2025 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica season. No damage sustained and testing resumed following standard vehicle inspection.	2025-02-18 16:50:00+05:30	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "During a private test session at Estoril, Chassis 001 experienced a minor off-track moment at Turn 6 while exploring setup limits with experimental damper settings. The car ran wide onto the asphalt runoff area, completing a controlled stop without contact with barriers or damage to the vehicle.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	0101000020E6100000AA6054522760434061545227A0C922C0	\N	\N	f	estoril-testing-off-track-excursion-2025	2026-04-10 10:45:54.806+05:30	2026-04-10 09:20:44.914+05:30
2	Portimão Qualifying Red Flag Incident 2025	portimao-quali-red-flag-2025	 Session interruption during qualifying for the 2025 Portimão round due to a competitor incident at Turn 1. AF Motorsport not directly involved but affected by session timing and tire preparation disruption.\n	2025-06-14 16:05:00+05:30	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "During the qualifying session at Autódromo Internacional do Algarve, a competitor car experienced brake failure approaching Turn 1, resulting in a high-speed off-track excursion into the gravel trap. The session was red-flagged for barrier inspection and vehicle recovery.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " Following standard safety protocols, the car returned to the pit lane for comprehensive inspection including suspension geometry verification, undertray examination, and tire condition assessment. No damage was identified and testing resumed within forty-five minutes.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The incident provided valuable data regarding the setup direction being evaluated and contributed to the team's understanding of the 992 GT3 Cup car's handling characteristics at Estoril. The off-track moment was correctly categorized as a learning opportunity within the controlled testing environment.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	0101000020E6100000AA6054522760434061545227A0C922C0	\N	\N	f	portimo-qualifying-red-flag-incident-2025	2026-04-10 10:46:41.785+05:30	2026-04-10 09:20:30.768+05:30
5	Barcelona Race 1 Contact Incident 2025	barcelona-race1-contact-2025	Minor contact during Race 1 of the 2025 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica round at Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya. The incident resulted in cosmetic damage only with no mechanical compromise or safety implications.	2025-04-26 20:15:00+05:30	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    During the opening lap of Race 1 at Barcelona, contact occurred between the AF Motorsport entry and a competitor's car at Turn 4 following an attempted overtaking maneuver. The contact was limited to wheel-to-wheel rubbing with no loss of control or position changes for either car.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Post-race inspection revealed minor cosmetic damage to the right-rear wheel arch and side skirt. No mechanical damage was sustained to suspension components, brake system, or drivetrain. The damage was repaired in the parc fermé period using approved materials and the car was cleared for Race 2 participation without penalty.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The incident was reviewed by Race Control with no further action taken. The contact was classified as a racing incident with no driver found predominantly at fault. The experience contributed to driver development regarding wheel-to-wheel positioning in tight corner complexes.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	0101000020E61000002FDD240681150240454772F90FC94440	\N	\N	f	barcelona-race-1-contact-incident-2025	2026-04-10 10:45:46.228+05:30	2026-04-10 09:20:58.506+05:30
3	Jerez Practice Electrical Issue 2025	jerez-practice-electrical-2025	Minor electrical system irregularity detected during Free Practice 1 at Circuito de Jerez. Issue identified and resolved without impact on subsequent sessions or competitive performance.\n	2025-07-11 15:15:00+05:30	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "During Free Practice 1 at Jerez, the Cosworth data system displayed intermittent communication errors with the Bosch ECU, resulting in data dropout during portions of the session. The issue did not affect vehicle performance or driver safety systems but compromised data collection for setup analysis.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Systematic diagnosis identified a loose connection at the data logger interface. The connection was secured and validated during the between-session service period. Full data functionality was restored for Free Practice 2 and all subsequent sessions.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The incident prompted a review of pre-session checklist procedures with additional verification steps added for data system connections. The quick diagnosis and resolution demonstrated the team's technical competence and the value of methodical troubleshooting protocols.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	0101000020E6100000DFE00B93A95A424000000000000020C0	\N	\N	f	jerez-practice-electrical-issue-2025	2026-04-10 10:46:26.287+05:30	2026-04-10 09:20:31.776+05:30
1	Estoril Finale Pit Stop Issue 2025	estoril-finale-pitstop-issue-2025	Delayed pit stop execution during a simulated race condition practice at the 2025 season finale weekend. The practice session incident identified procedural improvement opportunities without competitive impact.	2025-10-18 05:30:00+05:30	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": " During a simulated pit stop practice session at the Estoril finale, a procedural delay occurred when the right-rear wheel nut experienced cross-threading during reinstallation. The issue required removal and reinstallation, extending the practice stop duration beyond target parameters.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Root cause analysis identified that wheel gun operator positioning had varied slightly from standard procedure, contributing to the misalignment. The incident occurred during practice with no competitive impact, providing valuable learning without consequence.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The experience prompted enhanced pit stop procedure documentation including visual alignment guides for wheel gun positioning. Additional practice repetitions were scheduled to reinforce correct technique and build crew consistency. The incident exemplified the team's commitment to identifying improvement opportunities in all operational areas.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	0101000020E61000008048BF7D1D604340448B6CE7FBC922C0	\N	\N	f	estoril-finale-pit-stop-issue-2025	2026-04-10 10:47:01.002+05:30	2026-04-10 09:20:11.573+05:30
6	Gabriela Correia Off-Track Murça 2026	gabriela-correia-offtrack-murca-2026	description: Off-track excursion for Gabriela Correia during practice at Rampa Porca de Murça 2026, resulting in minor damage and a remarkable sub-30-minute repair by AF Motorsport mechanics.	2026-03-28 16:00:00+05:30	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "During a practice run on the challenging Murça hillclimb course, Gabriela Correia had an off-track moment in the Porsche 991.2 GT3 Cup. The car left the road at a medium-speed right-hand corner, making light contact with the barriers before coming to rest in a gravel trap.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The incident resulted in damage to the front splitter, right-front suspension components, and bodywork. Initial assessment suggested the weekend might be over, but AF Motorsport's mechanics executed an extraordinary repair effort. Working with precision and urgency, the team replaced damaged components, realigned suspension geometry, and returned the car to competitive condition in under 30 minutes.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The repair demonstrated AF Motorsport's exceptional preparation standards, comprehensive spares inventory, and the skill and dedication of the mechanical team. Correia returned to complete the weekend's competitive runs, a testament to both her resilience and the team's capability.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	0101000020E6100000F9A067B3EAB344401B9E5E29CBD01DC0	\N	\N	f	gabriela-correia-off-track-mura-2026	2026-04-10 16:21:22.917+05:30	2026-04-10 16:21:22.917+05:30
7	Pipo Massa Race 2 Retirement Barcelona	pipo-massa-barcelona-retirement	Pipo Massa forced out of Race 2 at Barcelona Winter Series finale due to contact from another competitor, ending his weekend after Race 1 victory.	2026-03-15 19:45:00+05:30	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Following the elation of his first European victory in Race 1, Pipo Massa's Barcelona weekend concluded prematurely in Race 2 when contact from a competitor forced his retirement from the event. The incident occurred at Turn 4, with another car making an over-optimistic overtaking attempt that resulted in wheel-to-wheel contact and suspension damage to the AF Motorsport Porsche.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The retirement was particularly disappointing given the momentum from the Race 1 victory and the strong pace demonstrated throughout the weekend. However, Pipo's response to the adversity demonstrated the maturity and professionalism that AF Motorsport values in its drivers.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Post-incident analysis focused on the many positives from the weekend—the victory, the wet-weather performance, and the continued development trajectory—rather than dwelling on an incident outside the team's control. The experience added another dimension to Pipo's racing education: managing the emotional swings inherent in motorsport competition.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	0101000020E6100000454772F90FC944402FDD240681150240	\N	\N	f	pipo-massa-race-2-retirement-barcelona	2026-04-10 16:23:24.673+05:30	2026-04-10 16:23:24.673+05:30
\.


