1	5	69d87b9d40b9fa0a0f55b476	What is the primary technical contact and escalation path for damper-related issues requiring urgent attention?	Race Engineer for immediate trackside issues, Technical Director for development matters, Commercial Director for partnership scope questions.	Clear communication pathways ensure efficient issue resolution and appropriate stakeholder involvement.
1	4	69d87b2455eef4b438b5aedb	What are the five core values of AF Motorsport that all academy drivers are expected to demonstrate?	Preparation, Respect, Continuous Improvement, Team Above Individual, Professional Conduct.	These values define the behavioral expectations and cultural foundation of participation in AF Motorsport programs.
1	3	69d8791969e146bab7877dff	Describe the primary setup parameters affecting high-speed understeer in the Porsche 992 GT3 Cup car.	Rear wing angle reduction, front ride height increase, or rear spring rate reduction depending on specific corner phase and circuit characteristics.	The 992 GT3 Cup responds to multiple setup adjustments for high-speed balance. Understanding the specific phase of understeer and the circuit context determines optimal adjustment path.
1	2	69d879c24917f56e6c75e31c	What is the correct torque sequence and specification for Porsche 992 GT3 Cup wheel installation?	 Cross-pattern sequence to 160 Nm, verify with second pass, mark fastener position per team protocol.	Proper torque sequence ensures even load distribution and prevents brake disc distortion. Second verification and marking are mandatory safety procedures.
1	1	69d879bc77a3d48442ffee03	Describe the tiered partner structure and key differences in activation rights between levels.	Title Partner receives primary brand placement and exclusive category rights. Technical Partners receive product association and technical content. Official Partners receive brand association and hospitality access. Activation rights scale accordingly.	Understanding partner tier structure ensures appropriate delivery of contracted benefits and prevents rights conflicts.
