COPY public.races (id, name, alias, basics_identifiers_code, basics_identifiers_abbreviation, basics_tagline, basics_description, details_history, details_type, details_status, details_start_date, details_end_date, details_event_id, details_season_id, details_series_id, details_circuit_id, details_laps, details_distance_km, details_winner_id, details_pole_position_id, details_fastest_lap_id, details_fastest_lap_time, details_weather, details_safety_car_periods, details_red_flags, details_notes, assets_thumbnail_id, assets_poster_id, assets_cover_id, assets_video_id, generate_slug, slug, updated_at, created_at) FROM stdin;
4	PSCI Portimão 2026 Race 1	psci-portimao-2026-race1	PSCI-2026-R3-R1	POR R1	Rollercoaster Challenge - Race 1	First race of the Portimão summer round at Autódromo Internacional do Algarve. The circuit's dramatic elevation changes and challenging layout provide one of the season's most demanding tests, with blind corners and high-speed crests rewarding driver commitment and precise car setup.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Portimão Race 1 places extraordinary demands on driver confidence and car preparation. The circuit's signature undulations require absolute commitment through blind sections while maintaining precision for the technical final sector. The layout provides multiple overtaking opportunities, with the heavy braking zone into Turn 1 and the run to Turn 5 presenting the primary passing locations.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    AF Motorsport's satellite facility at Portimão provides operational advantages including extensive circuit data and setup references. The team's strong historical performance at the circuit establishes Portimão as a key championship opportunity.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	sprint	scheduled	2026-06-13 20:00:00+05:30	2026-06-13 20:30:00+05:30	2	3	3	3	16	74.448	1	2	5	17:45:65	Winter	0	0	AF Motorsport satellite facility provides operational advantages. Historical team strength at circuit.	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	psci-portimo-2026-race-1	2026-04-10 18:00:21.538+05:30	2026-04-09 20:40:20.743+05:30
2	PSCI Estoril 2026 Race 2	psci-estoril-2026-race2	PSCI-2026-R1-R2	EST R2	Season Opener - Race 2	Second sprint race completing the Estoril season opener weekend. Grid positions determined by each driver's second-fastest qualifying lap per championship sporting regulations, creating potential variation from Race 1 starting order.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Race 2 at Estoril often produces more varied outcomes than the opening contest, with the alternative grid order creating different competitive dynamics. The Sunday race completes the first championship weekend, with drivers balancing aggression for position against the need to secure points for the season start.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The race's afternoon timing typically features warmer track temperatures than Race 1, affecting tire management strategies and potentially altering competitive balance. Teams must adapt setup and driving approach to the evolving conditions.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	sprint	scheduled	2026-03-29 20:30:00+05:30	2026-03-29 21:00:00+05:30	1	2	2	1	18	75.276	2	3	3	18:45:65	Winter	0	0	Grid from second-fastest qualifying laps. Sunday afternoon timing with potential temperature increase.	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	psci-estoril-2026-race-2	2026-04-10 18:04:42.375+05:30	2026-04-09 20:37:28.903+05:30
1	PSCI Estoril 2026 Race 1	psci-estoril-2026-race1	PSCI-2026-R1-R1	EST R1	Season Opener - Race 1	Opening race of the 2026 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica championship at Autódromo do Estoril. The 30-minute sprint race launches the season at AF Motorsport's home circuit, with full championship points awarded and the first indication of competitive order for the new campaign.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Race 1 at the Estoril season opener traditionally sets the championship narrative, providing the first competitive benchmark following winter development and pre-season testing. The race outcome often predicts championship trajectories while the Estoril layout's limited overtaking opportunities place premium on qualifying performance and race start execution.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    For AF Motorsport, the home race carries additional significance with extensive partner attendance, media focus, and the opportunity to establish early championship momentum. Strong performance at Estoril has historically correlated with successful season outcomes.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	sprint	scheduled	2026-03-28 20:00:00+05:30	2026-03-28 20:30:00+05:30	1	1	1	2	18	75.276	1	2	3	19:45:65	Winter	0	0	Home event for AF Motorsport. Standing start procedure. Full championship points awarded.	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	psci-estoril-2026-race-1	2026-04-10 18:05:37.883+05:30	2026-04-09 20:35:54.494+05:30
5	PSCI Barcelona 2026 Race 2	psci-barcelona-2026-race2	PSCI-2026-R2-R2	BCN R2	Catalan Challenge - Race 2	Second race of the Barcelona weekend completing the Spanish round. Grid determined by second-fastest qualifying laps creating potential variation from Race 1 starting order and strategic complexity.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Race 2 at Barcelona often features different competitive dynamics due to the alternative grid order. Drivers and teams apply learnings from Race 1 regarding tire behavior, aerodynamic setup effectiveness, and race pace to optimize Sunday performance.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The race provides final opportunity for championship points at the Spanish venue before the series returns to Portugal. Strategic approaches vary based on championship positions and individual objectives, with some drivers prioritizing points accumulation while others pursue victory.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	sprint	scheduled	2026-04-26 20:30:00+05:30	2026-04-26 21:00:00+05:30	2	2	2	3	14	65.198	2	3	3	14:45:65	Winter	0	0	Grid from second-fastest qualifying laps. Tire strategy informed by Race 1 degradation data. Final Spanish round race.\n	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	psci-barcelona-2026-race-2	2026-04-10 17:52:05.458+05:30	2026-04-10 10:09:48.469+05:30
8	GT Winter Series Round 4 Barcelona Race 1 2026	gtws-r4-barcelona-race1-2026	GTWS-2026-R4-R1	BCN R1	Massa Victory in Barcelona Wet	Race 1 of the GT Winter Series finale at Barcelona delivered a breakthrough victory for Pipo Massa in challenging wet conditions. The AF Motorsport Porsche 992 GT3 Cup entry, shared with Anders Steiner of Team Steiner Racing, secured Cup 2 class honors by a narrow margin.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Race 1 at Barcelona showcased Pipo Massa's continuing development as he mastered difficult wet conditions to secure his first European race victory. The AF Motorsport Porsche 992 GT3 Cup demonstrated strong pace throughout, with Massa managing the gap to pursuers masterfully in the closing laps.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The victory margin of just 0.637 seconds reflected the intensity of competition, but Massa's composure under pressure suggested a driver maturing rapidly. The result provided emotional validation for AF Motorsport's driver development philosophy and the Massa family's commitment to Pipo's racing education.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	sprint	completed	2026-03-14 15:30:00+05:30	2026-03-14 16:10:00+05:30	4	3	1	4	18	83.826	\N	\N	\N	01:52.347	Wet conditions, steady rain, 12°C ambient, 14°C track	0	0	First European victory for Pipo Massa. Winning margin 0.637 seconds. Exceptional wet-weather driving performance.	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	gt-winter-series-round-4-barcelona-race-1-2026	2026-04-10 17:44:01.799+05:30	2026-04-10 16:02:32.25+05:30
7	International GT Open Round 1 Portimão 2026	int-gt-open-r1-portimao-2026	IGTO-2026-R1	POR R1	GT Open Season Debut	The International GT Open commences its 2026 campaign at Portimão, with AF Motorsport fielding a Porsche 991.2 GT3 R for the driver pairing of André Fernandes and Angelo Fontana.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Portimão has become a traditional and popular venue for the International GT Open season opener. The circuit's combination of high-speed commitment and technical complexity provides an immediate test of championship aspirations.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    AF Motorsport's GT Open debut demonstrated the team's readiness for top-level European GT competition. The Fernandes-Fontana pairing showed strong pace and consistent performance, completing all sessions and races while gaining valuable experience with GT3 machinery at this level.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	feature	completed	2026-03-14 18:30:00+05:30	2026-03-14 19:40:00+05:30	2	4	3	1	25	116.325	\N	\N	\N	\N	Sunny, dry, 18°C ambient, 26°C track	0	0	AF Motorsport International GT Open debut. Clean race with consistent pace throughout.	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	international-gt-open-round-1-portimo-2026	2026-04-10 17:46:43.212+05:30	2026-04-10 16:00:04.297+05:30
6	GT Cup Europe Round 1 Portimão 2026	gt-cup-europe-r1-portimao-2026	GTCUP-2026-R1	POR R1	Season Opener at the Rollercoaster	The opening round of the 2026 GT Cup Europe championship at Autódromo Internacional do Algarve. AF Motorsport fields multiple entries in Cup class competition with drivers José Barros and Leonardo Reis making their international debuts.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Portimão provides a spectacular and demanding venue for the GT Cup Europe season opener. The circuit's dramatic elevation changes and challenging layout immediately test teams' off-season preparation and driver readiness for international competition.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    AF Motorsport's entries demonstrated competitive pace throughout the weekend, with both drivers adapting quickly to the demands of international GT competition. The event provided valuable experience and established a solid foundation for the championship campaign ahead.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	sprint	completed	2026-03-07 20:00:00+05:30	2026-03-07 20:50:00+05:30	4	3	2	2	16	74.448	\N	\N	\N	\N	Variable conditions with dry start and rain showers mid-race	1	0	International debuts for José Barros and Leonardo Reis. Challenging conditions tested driver adaptability.	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	gt-cup-europe-round-1-portimo-2026	2026-04-10 17:49:29.843+05:30	2026-04-10 15:58:40.306+05:30
3	PSCI Barcelona 2026 Race 1	psci-barcelona-2026-race1	PSCI-2026-R2-R1	BCN R1	Catalan Challenge - Race 1	First race of the Barcelona round, contested on the full 4.657-kilometer Grand Prix circuit. The race features the championship's longest lap and most demanding aerodynamic test, with the long main straight and heavy braking into Turn 1 creating the premier overtaking opportunity of the season.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Barcelona Race 1 requires strategic compromise between aerodynamic setup and straight-line speed. The circuit's combination of high-speed corners and the kilometer-long main straight presents conflicting demands that teams must balance based on grid position and championship considerations.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The race start demands precise execution, with the extended run to Turn 1 providing opportunity for position changes but increased risk as cars reach maximum velocity in close proximity. Tire degradation at Barcelona exceeds other championship venues, introducing strategic complexity in the closing laps.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	sprint	scheduled	2026-04-25 20:00:00+05:30	2026-04-25 20:30:00+05:30	4	3	2	2	14	65.198	2	3	5	16:45:65	Winter	0	0	Longest lap of championship. Significant tire management considerations.	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	psci-barcelona-2026-race-1	2026-04-10 18:02:55.411+05:30	2026-04-09 20:38:55.52+05:30
9	GT Winter Series Round 4 Barcelona Race 2 2026	gtws-r4-barcelona-race2-2026	GTWS-2026-R4-R2	BCN R2	Adversity Strikes After Triumph	Race 2 of the GT Winter Series finale saw Pipo Massa's weekend end prematurely following contact from another competitor, forcing retirement from the race. The result contrasted sharply with the Race 1 victory but provided valuable learning experience.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Following the elation of his first European victory, Race 2 delivered motorsport's characteristic unpredictability. Contact from a competitor forced Pipo Massa's retirement, ending the weekend on a disappointing note.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Despite the result, the weekend was assessed positively by AF Motorsport leadership. The pace demonstrated in Race 1 and the resilience shown in adversity both contributed to Pipo's development as a complete racing professional. The experience reinforced the importance of managing both triumph and disappointment with equal professionalism.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	sprint	completed	2026-03-15 19:30:00+05:30	2026-03-15 19:50:00+05:30	3	2	2	4	8	37.256	\N	\N	\N	\N	Drying conditions, overcast, 14°C ambient, 18°C track	1	0	Retirement due to contact from competitor. Valuable learning experience despite disappointing outcome.	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	gt-winter-series-round-4-barcelona-race-2-2026	2026-04-10 17:41:07.323+05:30	2026-04-10 16:04:39.956+05:30
