2	Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica 2025	psci-2025	PSCI-2025	PSCI 2025	AF Motorsport's Debut Porsche Campaign	The 2025 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica season marked AF Motorsport's inaugural campaign in Porsche competition and the team's first full season in international one-make GT racing. The season provided the foundation for the team's Porsche program, establishing operational standards, competitive benchmarks, and technical understanding essential for long-term success.	1	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The 2025 season represented a transformative year for AF Motorsport, transitioning from national competition to the unified Iberian Porsche championship. The campaign demonstrated the team's capability to compete at elevated levels, with multiple podium finishes validating the preparation standards and driver development approach.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Key achievements included the team's first Porsche victory at Estoril in June, two additional podium finishes at Portimão and Barcelona, and consistent top-five qualifying performance across the season. The campaign provided essential learning regarding the 992 GT3 Cup car's setup sensitivity, tire management characteristics, and race strategy optimization specific to the championship format.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The season established AF Motorsport as a credible competitor within the Porsche paddock, building relationships with Porsche Motorsport personnel, fellow competitors, and championship officials that have proven valuable for the team's continued development.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	18	12	Inaugural AF Motorsport Porsche campaign. Two race victories and four total podium finishes achieved.	\N	\N	f	porsche-sprint-challenge-ibrica-2025	2026-04-10 10:22:20.338+05:30	2026-04-09 19:48:27.784+05:30
3	Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica 2024	psci-2024	PSCI-2024	PSCI 2024	The Unified Championship Debuts	The 2024 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica season represented the first full year of unified competition following the merger of Portuguese and Spanish national series. The championship established its identity with a balanced calendar across both nations and introduced the new 992-generation GT3 Cup car to the series.	2	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The 2024 season was pivotal in establishing the unified championship's credentials. The merger brought together the strongest competitors from both national series, immediately elevating the competitive standard and creating compelling narratives as Portuguese and Spanish teams competed directly for overall honors.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The introduction of the 992 GT3 Cup car brought contemporary Porsche Motorsport technology to the championship, with enhanced aerodynamics, improved safety systems, and the sophisticated double-wishbone front suspension transforming the driving experience. Teams and drivers adapted to the new machinery throughout the season, with setup knowledge accumulating rapidly as data was shared across the paddock.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The season successfully demonstrated the viability of the unified Iberian format, with strong grid numbers, competitive racing, and positive feedback from competitors, circuits, and Porsche Motorsport stakeholders.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	16	10	Inaugural season of unified championship. Introduction of 992-generation GT3 Cup car.	\N	\N	f	porsche-sprint-challenge-ibrica-2024	2026-04-10 10:55:12.734+05:30	2026-04-09 19:49:18.086+05:30
6	Porsche Carrera Cup Italia 2025	cci-2025	CCI-2025	CCI 2025	Italy's Premier Porsche Championship	The 2025 Porsche Carrera Cup Italia season represented one of Europe's strongest national Porsche championships, featuring the 992 GT3 Cup car competing at Italy's most prestigious circuits. The series served as a benchmark for competitive standards and operational excellence within the Porsche Motorsport pyramid.	2	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The 2025 Carrera Cup Italia season maintained the championship's position as a premier national series within Porsche's European structure. The grid featured a combination of established Italian GT specialists, emerging international talent, and Porsche junior program drivers, creating exceptional competitive depth.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    While AF Motorsport did not compete directly in the 2025 season, the championship's technical regulations, sporting format, and performance benchmarks provided valuable reference points for the team's Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica program. Setup data and performance metrics from Carrera Cup Italia events informed AF Motorsport's development direction.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	22	12	Reference championship for technical benchmarking and performance analysis.	\N	\N	f	porsche-carrera-cup-italia-2025	2026-04-10 10:20:57.167+05:30	2026-04-09 19:52:06.006+05:30
5	Campeonato de Portugal de Velocidade 2024	cpv-2024	CPV-2024	CPV 2024	Portuguese National GT Competition	The 2024 Campeonato de Portugal de Velocidade season represented Portugal's premier national GT and touring car championship. The series provided a competitive platform across multiple classes, with AF Motorsport participating in selected events as part of the team's broader competitive program.	3	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The 2024 CPV season continued the championship's tradition as the cornerstone of Portuguese circuit racing. The multi-class format accommodated diverse machinery from GT4 specification to national touring car categories, creating varied competition throughout the field.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    AF Motorsport's participation in selected CPV events provided additional competitive mileage and the opportunity to compete at Portuguese circuits not featured on the Porsche Sprint Challenge calendar. The events also served to maintain the team's presence within the national motorsport community alongside the primary Porsche campaign.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	28	12	Multi-class national championship. AF Motorsport participated in selected events.	\N	\N	f	campeonato-de-portugal-de-velocidade-2024	2026-04-10 10:21:24.639+05:30	2026-04-09 19:51:07.01+05:30
4	Porsche Sprint Challenge Portugal 2023	pscp-2023	PSCP-2023	PSCP 2023	Final Season of National Championship Format	The 2023 Porsche Sprint Challenge Portugal season represented the final year of standalone national competition before the merger into the unified Iberian championship. The series provided accessible Porsche Cup competition at Portuguese circuits, serving as the entry point to Porsche Motorsport for Portuguese teams and drivers.	3	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The 2023 season maintained the successful formula established since the championship's inception, with events at Portugal's principal circuits including Estoril, Portimão, and Braga. The series continued to feature the proven 991.2 GT3 Cup car, providing reliable performance and established setup knowledge.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The season served as a transition period as teams prepared for the upcoming unified championship. Discussions regarding the merger were well advanced throughout the year, with competitors actively planning for the expanded 2024 calendar and the introduction of the 992-generation car.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    For the Portuguese motorsport community, the season represented both the conclusion of an era and the foundation for the enhanced opportunities the unified championship would provide.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	12	10	Final season of standalone Portuguese national championship. 991.2 GT3 Cup car utilized throughout.	\N	\N	f	porsche-sprint-challenge-portugal-2023	2026-04-10 10:21:52.662+05:30	2026-04-09 19:50:07.299+05:30
1	Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica 2026	psci-2026	PSCI-2026	PSCI 2026	The Third Season of Unified Iberian Competition	The 2026 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica season represents the championship's third year as a unified Iberian series and marks AF Motorsport's second full campaign in the championship. The season features an expanded six-round calendar spanning Portugal and Spain's premier circuits, with the series continuing to establish itself as the definitive GT platform in the region.	1	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The 2026 season builds upon the successful foundation established during the championship's first two unified seasons. Grid numbers have consistently increased as teams and drivers recognize the value proposition of the championship's professional presentation, competitive format, and direct connection to Porsche's international motorsport pyramid.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Key developments for 2026 include enhanced television coverage through extended broadcast agreements, introduction of additional driver categorization to maintain competitive balance, and continued refinement of the sporting regulations based on competitor feedback and evolving FIA standards.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    For AF Motorsport, the 2026 season represents an opportunity to consolidate the competitive progress demonstrated in 2025. The team has expanded to a two-car entry for selected events while maintaining focused engineering resources to maximize performance from the primary entry. Season objectives include consistent podium contention and championship position improvement.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	24	12	Season calendar subject to final FIA and national federation approvals. Balance of Performance adjustments may be applied per Porsche Motorsport technical directives.	\N	\N	f	porsche-sprint-challenge-ibrica-2026	2026-04-10 10:22:49.854+05:30	2026-04-09 19:46:31.639+05:30
\.


