4	Campeonato de Portugal de Velocidade	cpv	CPV	CPV	Portuguese National GT Championship	The Campeonato de Portugal de Velocidade is Portugal's premier national GT and touring car championship, sanctioned by FPAK. The series features multiple classes accommodating various GT and touring car specifications, providing a competitive platform for teams and drivers across the Portuguese motorsport landscape. The championship visits Portugal's principal circuits with events typically featuring multiple races per weekend.	Active	Public	The championship calendar comprises five to six events at Portuguese circuits including Estoril, Portimão, Braga, and Vila Real street circuit. Events feature multiple races with combined classifications across classes, providing extensive track time and competitive opportunities throughout the season.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The CPV represents the continuation of Portugal's national circuit racing tradition dating back to the 1960s. The championship has evolved through various iterations and class structures, currently providing a home for GT4, TCR, and various national specification categories.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The series serves as an important component of the Portuguese motorsport ecosystem, providing competitive opportunities for teams and drivers while maintaining the national racing heritage. The championship's position complements international series visiting Portugal by developing local talent and providing competitive outlets between major events.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	3	5	1966-05-01 17:00:00+05:30	1966-05-31 17:00:00+05:30	0101000020E61000001CEBE2361A604340992A1895D4C922C0	\N	\N	\N	f	campeonato-de-portugal-de-velocidade	2026-04-10 10:17:23.209+05:30	2026-04-09 19:54:05.271+05:30
3	Porsche Mobil 1 Supercup	porsche-supercup	PMSC	PMSC	The Ultimate One-Make GT Championship	The Porsche Mobil 1 Supercup represents the pinnacle of Porsche's global one-make racing pyramid, running as primary support to Formula 1 at selected European Grand Prix events. The championship features identical Porsche 992 GT3 Cup cars competing for substantial prize money and the prestige of being crowned Supercup champion. The series provides unparalleled exposure with global television coverage and the opportunity to compete in front of Formula 1 audiences and decision-makers.	Active	Public	The championship typically comprises eight rounds at Formula 1 European Grand Prix events, with each weekend featuring a single race of approximately 30 minutes duration. The limited track time places extraordinary premium on preparation and qualifying performance, with grid position often determining race outcome on circuits where overtaking is challenging.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Established in 1993 as a direct support series to Formula 1, the Porsche Supercup has evolved into the definitive proving ground for GT talent. Champions include numerous drivers who progressed to factory GT programs, prototype racing, and in some cases Formula 1 opportunities.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The series' position within Formula 1 weekends provides unmatched exposure and networking opportunities, with team principals, driver managers, and manufacturer representatives regularly present in the paddock. The competitive standard is exceptionally high, with many national Carrera Cup champions stepping up to Supercup competition.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	2	4	1993-05-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	0101000020E610000086C954C1A85C4840A167B3EA73B52240	\N	\N	\N	f	porsche-mobil-1-supercup	2026-04-10 10:18:56.326+05:30	2026-04-09 19:45:53.121+05:30
2	Porsche Carrera Cup Italia	porsche-carrera-cup-italia	CCI	CCI	Italy's Premier One-Make Championship	The Porsche Carrera Cup Italia represents Italy's highest level of one-make GT racing, forming a key component of Porsche Motorsport's European competition pyramid. The championship features the Porsche 992 GT3 Cup car competing at Italy's most prestigious circuits including Monza, Imola, and Mugello. The series enjoys significant manufacturer support and extensive television coverage, making it a destination championship for emerging GT talent.	Active	Public	The championship typically features six race weekends across the Italian motorsport calendar, with each event comprising two races including one endurance-format event per weekend. The series shares billing with major Italian motorsport events including the GT Italian Championship, maximizing exposure and providing drivers experience in high-profile race meeting environments.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "  Established in 2007, the Porsche Carrera Cup Italia has developed into one of Europe's strongest national Porsche championships. The series has launched numerous drivers into international GT competition and serves as a crucial stepping stone toward the Porsche Mobil 1 Supercup and factory driving opportunities.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The championship's position within Italian motorsport provides unique benefits including racing at world-renowned circuits and exposure to the passionate Italian motorsport audience. The series maintains close technical alignment with Porsche's international Cup specifications, ensuring that competitive performance in Italy translates directly to Carrera Cup and Supercup opportunities elsewhere.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	1	3	2007-04-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	0101000020E61000009FCDAACFD5CE464055302AA913902240	\N	\N	\N	f	porsche-carrera-cup-italia	2026-04-10 10:19:31.248+05:30	2026-04-09 19:44:11.38+05:30
1	Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica	porsche-sprint-challenge-iberica	PSCI	PSCI	The Pinnacle of Iberian Porsche Racing	The Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica is the premier one-make GT championship spanning Portugal and Spain, featuring the latest generation Porsche 992 GT3 Cup car. The series provides a professional competitive platform for drivers progressing through the Porsche Motorsport pyramid, offering sprint-format races at iconic Iberian circuits with comprehensive television coverage and manufacturer support. The championship serves as a direct pathway to the Porsche Mobil 1 Supercup and international Carrera Cup competitions.	Active	Public	The championship calendar comprises six race weekends across Portugal and Spain, with each event featuring two 30-minute sprint races. The format emphasizes driver skill and team execution, with limited practice time placing premium on efficient preparation and strong opening laps. Championship points are awarded to the top fifteen finishers in each race, with additional points for pole position and fastest lap.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica was established in 2023 through the merger of the Porsche Sprint Challenge Portugal and Porsche Sprint Challenge España, creating a unified Iberian championship. This consolidation elevated the competitive standard by combining the strongest teams and drivers from both nations into a single premier series.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The championship represents the entry point to Porsche's international one-make pyramid in the region, sitting below the Porsche Carrera Cup Italia and Porsche Mobil 1 Supercup. The series has quickly established itself as the reference for GT racing in Iberia, attracting top regional talent and international drivers seeking competitive seat time at iconic European circuits.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The 992 GT3 Cup car introduced for the 2024 season brought significant performance advancements including enhanced aerodynamics, the double-wishbone front suspension derived from the 911 RSR, and the latest Cosworth electronics package. These improvements have elevated the driving experience while maintaining the accessibility and reliability that characterize Porsche one-make racing.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	2	2023-03-01 17:00:00+05:30	2026-09-15 17:00:00+05:30	0101000020E61000001CEBE2361A604340992A1895D4C922C0	\N	\N	\N	f	porsche-sprint-challenge-ibrica	2026-04-10 10:20:02.92+05:30	2026-04-09 19:41:59.237+05:30
6	GT Cup Europe	gt-cup-europe	GTCUPE	GTCE	Accessible European GT Competition	GT Cup Europe provides a professional platform for GT4 and Cup-class machinery competing at premier European circuits. The championship emphasizes competitive parity and driver development within a cost-controlled framework.	Active	Private	The 2026 GT Cup Europe calendar features six events at leading circuits across Portugal, Spain, France, and Belgium. Each weekend comprises two 60-minute practice sessions, 30-minute qualifying, and two 50-minute sprint races with driver changes required for Pro-Am entries.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Established in 2020, GT Cup Europe has grown into a respected category within the European GT landscape, attracting teams and drivers from national championships seeking international competition. The series' focus on driver talent over budgetary advantage aligns with AF Motorsport's competitive philosophy.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The championship serves as an ideal stepping stone between national GT competition and premier international categories, providing drivers with experience at European circuits and exposure to professional race operations.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	2020-04-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	0101000020E610000045D8F0F44AB14440DE02098A1F630140	\N	\N	\N	f	gt-cup-europe	2026-04-10 15:50:51.567+05:30	2026-04-10 15:50:31.078+05:30
5	Iberian Historic Endurance	iberian-historic-endurance	IHE	IHE	Preserving Motorsport Heritage	The Iberian Historic Endurance series celebrates motorsport heritage through competition for period-correct historic racing cars at classic circuits across Portugal and Spain. The series caters to vehicles spanning multiple decades of motorsport history, with classes structured by era and specification. Events combine competitive track sessions with significant social and display elements, creating a festival atmosphere celebrating motorsport history.	Inactive	Public	The series calendar features four to five events annually at historic circuits including Estoril, Jerez, and Portimão. Events typically span two days with practice, qualifying, and multiple race sessions per class. The paddock environment emphasizes accessibility and heritage appreciation, with cars displayed for public viewing between sessions.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Established in 2010 by a consortium of historic racing enthusiasts, the Iberian Historic Endurance series has grown to become the reference for historic motorsport competition in the region. The series maintains strong relationships with circuit operators and motorsport federations, ensuring appropriate competitive conditions while preserving the character of historic racing.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The series' philosophy emphasizes enjoyment and preservation over outright competition, with sporting regulations designed to encourage participation while maintaining appropriate standards. Technical regulations require period-correct specifications with concessions for modern safety equipment.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	4	\N	2010-09-01 17:00:00+05:30	2010-09-30 17:00:00+05:30	0101000020E61000001CEBE2361A604340992A1895D4C922C0	\N	\N	\N	f	iberian-historic-endurance	2026-04-10 10:18:04.07+05:30	2026-04-09 19:55:20.978+05:30
7	International GT Open	international-gt-open	IGTO	GT Open	Europe's Premier GT Championship	The International GT Open is one of Europe's leading GT championships, featuring GT3 machinery competing at iconic circuits including Portimão, Spa-Francorchamps, Monza, and Barcelona. The series attracts factory-supported and independent teams with professional driver lineups.	Active	Private	The 2026 International GT Open calendar spans seven European rounds from March through October. Each event features two 70-minute races with mandatory driver changes, success ballast based on championship position, and full FIA GT3 technical regulations.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Established in 2006 by GT Sport Organización, the International GT Open has developed into a benchmark for professional GT competition. The championship has launched numerous drivers to factory GT programs and global endurance racing success.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    AF Motorsport's participation in 2026 represents the team's continued progression within the Porsche Motorsport pyramid and provides valuable experience at Europe's most demanding circuits. The championship's professional standards and competitive depth create an ideal environment for organizational development.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	2006-04-01 17:00:00+05:30	\N	0101000020E610000045D8F0F44AB14440DE02098A1F630140	\N	\N	\N	f	international-gt-open	2026-04-10 15:52:16.873+05:30	2026-04-10 15:52:16.873+05:30
8	GT Winter Series	gt-winter-series	GTWS	GTWS	European Winter Competition	The GT Winter Series provides competitive racing opportunities during the traditional European off-season, with events at Southern European circuits offering favorable winter climate. The series features GT3, GT4, and Cup class machinery across multiple categories including overall, class, and junior classifications.	Active	Private	The 2026 GT Winter Series calendar includes four rounds at circuits in Portugal and Spain, running from January through March. Events feature sprint races, endurance formats, and combined classifications with multiple classes competing simultaneously. The Barcelona round serves as the traditional season finale.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The GT Winter Series, organized by GEDLICH Racing, has become an essential component of European motorsport calendars since its establishment in 2019. The series provides teams valuable testing and competition during winter months when most championships are dormant.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The Barcelona season finale represents the series' marquee event, consistently attracting international entries including former Formula 1 drivers, factory GT competitors, and emerging talent seeking competitive mileage. AF Motorsport's participation with Felipe and Pipo Massa generated significant media attention and fan engagement.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	\N	\N	2019-01-10 17:00:00+05:30	2026-03-15 17:00:00+05:30	0101000020E61000002E90A0F8310E4940053411363C5D2140	\N	\N	\N	f	gt-winter-series	2026-04-10 15:53:33.297+05:30	2026-04-10 15:53:33.297+05:30
\.


