COPY public.sessions (id, name, alias, basics_identifiers_code, basics_segment, basics_description, details_access, details_specification, details_history, details_notes, metrics_quantifiers_laps, metrics_quantifiers_distance, metrics_quantifiers_duration, metrics_quantifiers_interval, metrics_quantifiers_specification, assets_thumbnail_id, generate_slug, slug, updated_at, created_at) FROM stdin;
1	PSCI Estoril 2026 - Free Practice 1	psci-estoril-2026-fp1	PSCI-2026-R1-FP1	Free Practice	Opening practice session of the 2026 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica season at Autódromo do Estoril. This 45-minute session provides the first competitive running of the year, enabling teams to validate setup direction, bed in new components, and establish baseline performance references for the weekend.	private	Standard free practice format with open pit lane for session duration. No restrictions on tire usage or fuel load. Overtaking permitted with standard sporting regulations applying. Session may be red-flagged for incidents or safety concerns with time not recovered.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Free Practice 1 at the season opener carries particular significance as teams transition from pre-season testing to competitive running. The session often reveals relative performance levels obscured during private testing, providing first indication of competitive order for the new season.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    For AF Motorsport, the session focuses on validating the car's baseline setup derived from winter testing, ensuring systems function correctly, and providing the driver with reference points and confidence ahead of qualifying. Data collection priorities include tire behavior on green track surface and brake system performance under sustained running.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Track typically green with limited rubber deposition. Fuel load and tire allocation unrestricted.	22	92.004	45	0	Session duration measured in minutes. Laps and distance represent typical completion for lead driver during unrestricted practice session.	\N	f	psci-estoril-2026---free-practice-1	2026-04-09 20:02:40.878+05:30	2026-04-09 20:02:40.877+05:30
3	PSCI Estoril 2026 - Qualifying	psci-estoril-2026-quali	PSCI-2026-R1-QUAL	Qualifying	Official qualifying session determining the starting grid for both races of the Estoril weekend. The 30-minute session establishes grid position for Race 1, with each driver's fastest lap setting their Race 2 starting position under championship sporting regulations.	private	30-minute qualifying session with all cars on track simultaneously. Standard sporting regulations apply including track limits enforcement and minimum lap time requirements. Fastest single lap determines grid position for Race 1. Second-fastest lap from each driver determines Race 2 grid per championship format.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Estoril qualifying places premium on clean lap execution, with traffic management critical on the relatively short 4.182-kilometer layout. Finding clear track space while maintaining tire temperature for optimal single-lap performance requires strategic session management and effective communication between driver and engineer.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Grid position at Estoril carries elevated importance due to the circuit's challenging overtaking characteristics. The combination of high-speed corners in the first sector and the technical final section limits passing opportunities, making qualifying performance a strong predictor of race outcomes.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Two timed laps determine Race 1 and Race 2 grid positions. Traffic management critical.	8	33.456	30	5	Lap count includes out laps, timed laps, and in laps. Typically two complete timed run sequences per session.	\N	f	psci-estoril-2026---qualifying	2026-04-10 10:29:11.185+05:30	2026-04-09 20:05:39.161+05:30
2	PSCI Estoril 2026 - Free Practice 2	psci-estoril-2026-fp2	PSCI-2026-R1-FP2	Free Practice	Second practice session of the Estoril weekend, typically scheduled for Saturday morning ahead of qualifying. Track conditions evolve significantly from Friday running, with increased rubber deposition improving grip levels and altering setup requirements.	private	Standard free practice format with 45-minute duration. Teams typically focus on qualifying preparation including new tire evaluation and low-fuel running to establish qualifying performance potential.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Free Practice 2 serves as the final preparation before qualifying, with session priorities shifting from broad setup validation to specific qualifying and race preparation. Teams evaluate performance on fresh tires, validate qualifying engine modes and procedures, and simulate qualifying runs to prepare drivers for the intensity of single-lap performance extraction.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The session also provides opportunity to evaluate setup changes implemented overnight based on FP1 data analysis. Track evolution through the session often mirrors the progression expected during qualifying, enabling drivers to anticipate grip level changes.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Final preparation before qualifying. New tire evaluation priority.	20	83.64	45	0	Slightly reduced lap count compared to FP1 due to qualifying simulation runs requiring in and out laps.	\N	f	psci-estoril-2026---free-practice-2	2026-04-10 10:29:32.949+05:30	2026-04-09 20:04:08.867+05:30
7	PSCI Barcelona 2026 - Free Practice 2	psci-barcelona-2026-fp2	PSCI-2026-R2-FP2	Free Practice	Second practice session at Barcelona, scheduled ahead of qualifying. Focus shifts to qualifying simulation and race pace evaluation on long runs.	private	Standard 45-minute free practice format. Qualifying preparation includes new tire evaluation and low-fuel running.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Free Practice 2 at Barcelona emphasizes qualifying preparation due to the circuit's challenging overtaking characteristics. Grid position carries elevated importance, with the session providing final opportunity to optimize setup for single-lap performance.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Long run simulations evaluate tire degradation characteristics essential for race strategy. Barcelona's abrasive surface produces more significant degradation than other championship venues, making race pace evaluation critical.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Qualifying simulation priority. Tire degradation data collection for race strategy.	16	74.512	45	0	Reduced lap count due to qualifying simulation runs requiring out and in lap procedures.	\N	f	psci-barcelona-2026---free-practice-2	2026-04-09 20:10:04.926+05:30	2026-04-09 20:10:04.926+05:30
6	PSCI Barcelona 2026 - Free Practice 1	psci-barcelona-2026-fp1	PSCI-2026-R2-FP1	Free Practice	Opening practice session at Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya. The 4.657-kilometer Grand Prix circuit demands aerodynamic efficiency and precise setup, with initial running focused on establishing baseline balance for the unique demands of the Catalan venue.	private	Standard 45-minute free practice format. Open pit lane with unrestricted tire and fuel usage. Full circuit configuration utilized.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Barcelona Free Practice 1 provides essential data for setup direction at a circuit where aerodynamic performance significantly influences competitiveness. The session enables evaluation of downforce levels and balance characteristics through high-speed corners including the demanding Turn 9 right-hander.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Track conditions typically evolve rapidly at Barcelona as rubber deposition increases grip levels. Initial running may feature lower grip than anticipated, requiring setup adjustments throughout the session.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Track evolution significant through session. Aerodynamic balance evaluation priority.	18	83.826	45	0	Fewer laps than Estoril due to longer circuit length. Emphasis on quality timed runs over quantity.	\N	f	psci-barcelona-2026---free-practice-1	2026-04-10 10:27:57.216+05:30	2026-04-09 20:08:40.906+05:30
10	PSCI Barcelona 2026 - Race 2	psci-barcelona-2026-race2	PSCI-2026-R2-RACE2	Race	Second race of the Barcelona weekend completing the Spanish round. Grid determined by second-fastest qualifying laps creating potential variation from Race 1 starting order.	private	30-minute sprint race with grid from second-fastest qualifying times. Full championship points awarded.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Race 2 at Barcelona often features different competitive dynamics due to the alternative grid order. Drivers and teams apply learnings from Race 1 regarding tire behavior and race pace to optimize Sunday performance.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The race provides final opportunity for championship points at the Spanish venue before the series returns to Portugal. Strategic approaches vary based on championship positions and individual objectives.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Grid from second-fastest qualifying laps. Tire strategy informed by Race 1 data.	14	65.198	30	0	Identical race distance and duration to Race 1. Grid from second-fastest qualifying times.	\N	f	psci-barcelona-2026---race-2	2026-04-09 20:13:04.121+05:30	2026-04-09 20:13:04.121+05:30
11	PSCI Portimão 2026 - Free Practice 1	psci-portimao-2026-fp1	PSCI-2026-R3-FP1	Free Practice	Opening practice at Autódromo Internacional do Algarve. The circuit's dramatic elevation changes and challenging layout demand immediate driver acclimatization and setup validation for the unique characteristics of the Algarve venue.	private	Standard 45-minute free practice format. Full circuit configuration including signature elevation changes and blind crests.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Portimão Free Practice 1 prioritizes driver confidence building through the circuit's challenging sections. The blind Turn 5 crest and the compression through Turns 10 and 11 require commitment that develops with seat time.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Setup validation focuses on high-speed stability through the undulating first sector while maintaining mechanical grip through the technical final corners. AF Motorsport's satellite facility at Portimão provides extensive reference data for setup optimization.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Driver confidence building priority. Setup validation for unique elevation characteristics.	20	93.06	45	0	Higher lap count achievable due to circuit's flowing nature and limited traffic at typical test venue.	\N	f	psci-portimo-2026---free-practice-1	2026-04-10 10:26:35.799+05:30	2026-04-09 20:14:08.757+05:30
9	PSCI Barcelona 2026 - Race 1	psci-barcelona-2026-race1	PSCI-2026-R2-RACE1	Race	First race of the Barcelona weekend, utilizing the full 4.657-kilometer Grand Prix circuit. The race features the championship's longest lap and most demanding aerodynamic test, with the long main straight and heavy braking into Turn 1 creating the series' premier overtaking opportunity.	private	30-minute sprint race from standing start. Full championship format with points awarded to top fifteen finishers plus pole position and fastest lap bonuses.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Barcelona Race 1 often produces strategic variation as teams balance aerodynamic setup compromises. Higher downforce configurations benefit high-speed corner performance but reduce straight-line speed, affecting both overtaking and defending capabilities through Turn 1. The optimal compromise varies based on grid position and championship considerations.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The race start demands precise execution, with the long run to Turn 1 providing extended opportunity for position changes but also increased risk as cars reach maximum speed in close proximity. Tire degradation is typically more pronounced at Barcelona than at other championship venues, introducing strategic complexity in the closing laps.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Longest lap of championship. Significant tire management considerations.	14	65.198	30	0	Race distance of 14 laps covering 65.198 kilometers. Tire degradation management critical.	\N	f	psci-barcelona-2026---race-1	2026-04-10 10:26:55.318+05:30	2026-04-09 20:12:03.815+05:30
13	PSCI Portimão 2026 - Qualifying	psci-portimao-2026-quali	PSCI-2026-R3-QUAL	Qualifying	Qualifying session at Autódromo Internacional do Algarve, widely considered the championship's most demanding single-lap challenge. The circuit's dramatic elevation changes, blind crests, and technical complexity place extraordinary premium on driver confidence and precise car setup.	private	30-minute qualifying session determining grids for both Portimão races. Track limits strictly enforced particularly through the final sector where corner exit violations compromise lap validity.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Portimão qualifying separates drivers based on commitment through blind corners, particularly the daunting Turn 5 crest and the compression through Turns 10 and 11. The circuit's layout provides limited clear-track opportunity, requiring strategic session management to avoid traffic during critical qualifying attempts.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "    Setup refinement at Portimão requires compromise between high-speed stability through the undulating first sector and mechanical grip through the technical final corners. Teams with extensive circuit data, including AF Motorsport through its satellite facility, hold significant advantage in achieving this balance.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Premium on driver commitment through blind sections. AF Motorsport satellite facility provides data advantage.	8	37.224	30	0	Lap count includes out laps, timed laps, and in laps. Two complete timed run sequences typical.	\N	f	psci-portimo-2026---qualifying	2026-04-10 10:25:47.797+05:30	2026-04-09 20:17:04.123+05:30
12	PSCI Portimão 2026 - Free Practice 2	psci-portimao-2026-fp2	PSCI-2026-R3-FP2	Free Practice	Second practice session at Portimão ahead of qualifying. Focus shifts to qualifying preparation and race pace simulation on the challenging Algarve layout.	public	Standard 45-minute free practice format. Qualifying simulation and long run evaluation.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Free Practice 2 at Portimão emphasizes qualifying preparation, with the circuit's limited overtaking opportunities placing premium on grid position. New tire evaluation and low-fuel running establish qualifying performance potential.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Race pace simulation evaluates tire degradation characteristics on a circuit that stresses tires through high-speed direction changes and heavy braking zones. The data informs race strategy and setup compromises.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Qualifying simulation priority. Tire degradation evaluation for strategic planning.	18	83.754	45	0	Slightly reduced lap count due to qualifying simulation runs.	\N	f	psci-portimo-2026---free-practice-2	2026-04-10 10:26:15.589+05:30	2026-04-09 20:15:16.269+05:30
8	PSCI Barcelona 2026 - Qualifying	psci-barcelona-2026-quali	PSCI-2026-R2-QUAL	Qualifying	Qualifying session for the Barcelona round of the 2026 Porsche Sprint Challenge Ibérica championship. The circuit layout demands aerodynamic efficiency and precise setup, with qualifying performance heavily influenced by car balance through the high-speed Turn 9 and traction from the final chicane.	private	30-minute qualifying session with standard championship format determining Race 1 and Race 2 grid positions from fastest and second-fastest laps respectively.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Barcelona qualifying emphasizes the 992 GT3 Cup car's aerodynamic performance, with the long main straight and high-speed corners rewarding efficient downforce and stable platform control. Drivers must manage tire preparation carefully, as the circuit's abrasive surface can degrade performance across multiple qualifying attempts.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Track evolution at Barcelona is pronounced, with lap times typically improving throughout the session as rubber deposition increases. The optimal qualifying strategy often involves an initial banker lap followed by a single additional attempt on fresh tires late in the session when track conditions peak.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Significant track evolution through session. Single-lap performance critical due to circuit length.	7	32.599	30	0	Lower lap count due to circuit length. Typically two complete timed run sequences.	\N	f	psci-barcelona-2026---qualifying	2026-04-10 10:27:21.003+05:30	2026-04-09 20:10:55.571+05:30
5	PSCI Estoril 2026 - Race 2	psci-estoril-2026-race2	PSCI-2026-R1-RACE2	Race	Second sprint race completing the Estoril weekend program. Grid positions are determined by each driver's second-fastest qualifying lap, creating potential variation from Race 1 starting order and strategic complexity for championship contenders.	private	30-minute sprint race with grid determined by second-fastest qualifying times. Standing start procedure identical to Race 1. Full championship points awarded. Event classification combines Race 1 and Race 2 results for weekend honors.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Race 2 at Estoril often produces more varied outcomes than the opening contest, with the alternative grid order creating different competitive dynamics. Drivers who maximized their second qualifying lap may find themselves in stronger grid positions than their Race 1 performance would indicate.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    The Sunday race typically features more aggressive driving as competitors adapt to established weekend conditions and pursue final opportunities for championship points. Tire management may be complicated by higher track temperatures during afternoon sessions, requiring adjustment to driving technique and strategic approach.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Grid from second-fastest qualifying laps. Sunday afternoon timing with potential temperature variation.	18	75.276	30	0	Identical race distance and duration to Race 1. Grid determined by second-fastest qualifying lap per championship regulations.	\N	f	psci-estoril-2026---race-2	2026-04-10 10:28:26.555+05:30	2026-04-09 20:07:53.918+05:30
4	PSCI Estoril 2026 - Race 1	psci-estoril-2026-race1	PSCI-2026-R1-RACE1	Race	First sprint race of the Estoril weekend and opening race of the 2026 championship. The 30-minute contest awards full championship points and sets the competitive tone for the season ahead.	private	30-minute sprint race from standing start. Formation lap precedes race start with rolling start procedure. No mandatory pit stop. Full championship points awarded to top fifteen finishers with additional points for pole position and fastest lap.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Race 1 at the season opener carries unique pressure as drivers balance championship point accumulation against the need to complete the first race without incident. The standing start at Estoril requires precise clutch engagement and wheelspin management, with the run to Turn 1 demanding commitment while avoiding contact in the tightly-bunched opening laps.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "    Tire management across the 30-minute duration requires strategic discipline, with degradation typically manageable at Estoril under normal conditions. The race often features strategic variation in tire preparation and early-race aggression levels as teams optimize their championship positions.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}	Standing start procedure. Full championship points awarded. No mandatory pit stop.	18	75.276	30	0	Race distance of 18 laps covering 75.276 kilometers. Duration of 30 minutes with one additional lap after leader completes scheduled distance.	\N	f	psci-estoril-2026---race-1	2026-04-10 10:28:48.316+05:30	2026-04-09 20:06:46.277+05:30
