COPY public.statuses (id, name, alias, basics_description, generate_slug, slug, updated_at, created_at) FROM stdin;
1	Inactive	inactive	Designates an entity that is temporarily not participating or operational but remains associated with the organization and may return to active status. This status applies to drivers taking sabbaticals or recovering from injury, team members on extended leave, cars undergoing major rebuilds or preservation, and programs temporarily suspended due to external factors. Unlike Retired or Archived statuses, Inactive implies a clear pathway to reactivation and continued association with the team. Entities with Inactive status maintain their relationships and historical data connections but are typically excluded from current operational views and active rosters until status changes.	f	inactive	2026-04-09 18:43:55.892+05:30	2026-04-09 18:43:55.891+05:30
2	Retired	retired	Indicates permanent cessation of competitive or operational activity with no expectation of return to active duty. For drivers, this status marks the end of professional racing career, whether by choice, circumstance, or age. For cars, it denotes vehicles no longer used in competition and transitioned to museum, collection, or display roles. For leaders and members, it signifies formal retirement from professional motorsport involvement. Retired status preserves all historical relationships, achievements, and contributions while clearly communicating that the entity is no longer active in current operations.	f	retired	2026-04-09 18:45:04.857+05:30	2026-04-09 18:45:04.857+05:30
3	Development	development	Signifies an entity in active preparation, construction, or evolution toward operational readiness but not yet deployed in competitive or production contexts. This status applies to cars undergoing design and build phases, drivers progressing through academy or junior programs, facilities under construction, and plans in detailed formulation stages. Development status indicates active investment of resources and forward progress while clearly communicating that the entity is not yet ready for its ultimate intended purpose. For cars, this includes prototype, testing, and validation phases. For personnel, it encompasses training, evaluation, and preparation periods before competitive deployment.	f	development	2026-04-09 18:45:19.572+05:30	2026-04-09 18:45:19.571+05:30
4	Suspended	suspended	Represents temporary removal from active participation due to regulatory, disciplinary, or administrative action. This status is applied to drivers serving competition bans, team members under investigation, or entities temporarily barred from participation by series officials or team management. Suspended status carries specific temporal boundaries with defined start and anticipated end dates, distinguishing it from Inactive status which is typically voluntary or circumstantial rather than imposed. During suspension, entities maintain their relationships and records but are restricted from participation in designated activities. The status implies a formal process for reinstatement upon completion of suspension terms.	f	suspended	2026-04-09 18:45:22.935+05:30	2026-04-09 18:45:22.935+05:30
5	Archived	archived	Designates content, records, or entities that have been preserved for historical reference but are no longer active in current operations. This status applies to completed seasons, concluded championships, former regulations, outdated policies, and historical documents. Archived entities maintain full data integrity and relationships but are typically filtered from active management views and current operational interfaces. The status indicates that while the information remains valuable for reference, analysis, and historical context, it should not appear in active selection lists, current rosters, or default content displays. Archived status differs from deletion in that data remains fully accessible and queryable when specifically requested.	f	archived	2026-04-09 18:45:46.996+05:30	2026-04-09 18:45:46.996+05:30
6	Active	active	Indicates that an entity is currently operational, participating, or engaged in its designated function. For drivers, this status means currently competing in races or series. For team members, it denotes current employment and active involvement in team operations. For cars, it signifies the vehicle is race-ready and in current competitive use. For plans and programs, it indicates ongoing execution and current relevance. The Active status is the default operational state for most entities and implies full availability, participation, and engagement in all normal activities and responsibilities associated with the role or asset.	f	active	2026-04-09 18:46:20.158+05:30	2026-04-09 18:46:20.157+05:30
7	Pending	pending	Indicates an entity awaiting approval, confirmation, or completion of prerequisite conditions before transitioning to Active status. This status applies to driver contracts awaiting final signature, entries awaiting confirmation from series organizers, plans awaiting budget approval, and members completing onboarding requirements. Pending status serves as a holding state that acknowledges the entity's existence and anticipated activation while preventing premature inclusion in active operational contexts. The status implies forward momentum toward activation and typically includes expected resolution timelines or outstanding requirements that must be satisfied before status advancement.	f	pending	2026-04-09 18:46:20.487+05:30	2026-04-09 18:46:20.487+05:30
\.


